title: peanut brittle
directions: Spread peanuts in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Place in a 350° oven for 15 minutes. Remove and pour into bowl.
Keep warm.

title: almond-coconut cream pie
directions: Process cookies in food processor to make fine crumbs.
Add butter; process to blend.
Press in 9 inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly toasted around edge.
Cool on wire rack.

title: kentucky coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add coconut, sugar, melted margarine, vinegar and vanilla. Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until brown.

title: kebabs
directions: You will also need 1 package of skewers.

title: almond green beans
directions: Simmer green beans in salted water to cover for 15 minutes. Saute almonds in 1 tablespoon oil until lightly browned; remove. Add rest of oil to pan.
Add flour to thicken.
Stir constantly. Add yogurt.
Mix until smooth.
Cook until thickened.
Add drained beans.
Add other ingredients.
Serve.

title: watergate pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, mix baking powder into sugar and add slowly to egg whites.
Add vanilla, fold in crumbs and nuts.
Pour into crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then put pie in refrigerator overnight (must be done).
Remove 10 or 15 minutes before serving with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the margarine with brown and white sugars.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add sifted flour and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry crunch crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients by cutting in the butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Place cherry pie filling in baking dish; sprinkle topping mixture on top.
Cook in preheated oven (375°) until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm.
May serve with ice cream.

title: fiesta salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Pour over vegetables; mix gently.
Chill 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with additional picante sauce if desired.

title: chewy delight
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, oleo and nuts with hands until crumbly. Spread on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take cream cheese, confectioners sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy and pour over top of first mixture.
Bake about 40 minutes in 325° oven.
Cool slightly before cutting into squares.

title: no-sugar raisin-apple pie
directions: In saucepan, combine raisins, apples, sweetener, lemon juice and water; bring to boil, turn heat down and simmer 10 minutes. Now stir in cornstarch which has been mixed with enough cold water to make it into liquid (approximately 3 or 4 tablespoons).
Pie filling should be thickening.
Pour into pie shell, dot with oleo, add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut vegetables up in 1 1/2 x 2-inch pieces.
(Potatoes usually are cooked separately.) Bake at 350° for at least 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
When cooked, add potatoes and let flavor for 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread and ground meat
directions: Beat eggs; mix corn meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt and corn. Set aside. Saute ground meat in 2 teaspoons oil; drain grease. Prepare place in separate mounds chopped onions, grated cheese and chopped peppers. Grease large skillet.

Sprinkle 2 teaspoons corn meal in skillet; let brown. Pour 1/2 of batter in skillet. Sprinkle cheese evenly over batter, then meat, onion and pepper on top. Pour remaining batter on top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: walnut carrot raisin loaf
directions: Mix in order that they are listed.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: diabetic pie crust
directions: Squeeze cottage cheese through a sieve.
Cut shortening into flour
and	salt
until
the
consistency
of meal.
Add cottage cheese
and mix well with a fork until a ball of dough forms. Roll on lightly floured parsley cloth.
This will make 1 (8
or 9-inch)
crust.
To bake the pie shell, cook at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Trim off excess fat from pork chops.
Make a slit to form a pocked in fat end of each pork chop.

title: old fashioned butter cookies
directions: In mixing bowl combine butter, sugar and egg.
Beat on medium until light and fluffy.
Reduce speed.
Stir in flour, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and well combined.
Chill 2 to 3 hours until firm enough to be rolled. Roll out dough to 1/8 to 1/4 inch thickness on floured surface. Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost or decorate.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift together the first four ingredients.
In a large bowl, cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add pineapple, nuts and flour mixture; mix well.
Add vanilla; drop rounded teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave chicken breasts
directions: Shake pepper, salt and garlic over each breast.
Mix wine, Worcestershire and oregano.
Put chicken in shallow casserole. Pour wine mixture over; cover with plastic wrap (punctured). Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: pecan pie(black walnut)
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add syrup, eggs, butter and flavoring. Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer, or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: old testament scripture cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, beating until light.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.

Beat in the honey. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the milk and beat only until smooth. Stir in nuts and fruits. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into a 9 x 5 x 13-inch loaf pan lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Turn and peel off paper. Cool cake right side up.

title: lib p's pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, water, salt and butter for 5 minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons of water.
Add to raisin mixture and cook for 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat and add lemon extract.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Cover with lattice crust top.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°*.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Set aside.

title: sausage hash brown breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring until sausage crumbles and is no longer pink.
Drain well.
Prepare hash browns according to package directions, using 1/2 tsp. salt & pepper.
Stir together hash browns, sausage and cheese.
Pour into a lightly greased 13x9-inch baking dish.
Whisk together eggs, milk and remaining teaspoon of salt.
Pour evenly over potato mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: saucy franks
directions: Brown scored dogs in buttered skillet.
Add ingredients, except peppers.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Then add peppers and cook 5 minutes. Pour over cooked noodles.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press into pan lined with waxed paper.
Decorate with candied fruit.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Wrap securely; store in refrigerator.
Will keep several weeks.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl.
Slowly add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue mixing until thick and foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mix into yolks, return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes and stir constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover with wax paper.
Cut bananas into pie shell. Pour mixture over bananas.
Top with meringue.
Bake in oven at 350° until meringue is golden.

title: soupe 'a l'oignon au gratin(french onion soup with cheese)
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add sugar and nutmeg.
Toss well.
Cook down slightly until onions are a golden color.
Add hot bouillon and bring to a boil.
Add wine.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt if needed or to taste.
Ladle soup into 6 ovenproof bowls or pots and top each with 1 piece of bread and grated cheese.
Cook in preheated 300° oven for 10 minutes or under broiler until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: steamed chicken
directions: In a large pot, mix together half water and half vinegar to about two inches depth.
Remove skin from chicken and place it on some type of rack above the liquid (a colander works well). Cover chicken with Old Bay as you would when steaming crabs, being sure to season every layer.
Cover pot tightly and steam until starts to pull away from the bone.
You may have to rotate chicken as it steams to ensure all pieces are done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash shrimp.
Mix with sour cream and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour with a pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Add buttermilk, stirring the mixture just until moistened.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch round cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 14 minutes or until golden.
Brush the hot biscuits with melted butter.

title: chop suey bake
directions: Brown meat in oil (oil is needed if using pork steak, which is best).
Add onion, green pepper and celery, then mix all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
May make in electric frypan on low for 1 hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Clean strawberries and remove the stems.
Rinse strawberries in cold water several times.
Place strawberries in bowl. Sprinkle sugar onto strawberries.
Using a potato masher or fork, mash the strawberries with sugar.
In a small bowl, whisk sour cream to remove lumps.
Mix sour cream with strawberries until thoroughly blended.
Mixture should be pale pink.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Put beans and water in pan and bring to boiling.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Brown chicken slowly in oil; sprinkle with salt.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sherry wine, mushrooms, bay leaves and garlic.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, until chicken is tender. Uncover.
Add drained onions and olives; simmer rapidly until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, water and white Karo to a boil, then add raw peanuts.
Cook until forms a soft ball in a cup of water.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo, vanilla, salt and red food coloring.
Beat until thick and will start to turn pink.
Then drop on wax paper.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Drain and mash pintos.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 1` hour.
Let cool 30 minutes.

title: grandmother's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Gradually add 3 c. flour. Pour 1 c. over fruits and nuts that have been chopped and mixed together in large dishpan.
Sprinkle fruit cake spice over fruit and nuts and then pour in cake mixture.
Mix and bake in 350 degree oven.
Makes 1 large and 2 small cakes.

title: cinnamon walnuts
directions: Bring to a boil.
Stir in 2 pounds walnut halves and coat well.
Spread on a cookie sheet, turning occasionally to dry.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Crumble potato chips in blender; set aside.
Put chicken and celery in casserole.
Put mayonnaise, cheese, lemon and onion into blender.
Cover and process until smooth.
Add almonds and process only until chopped.
Pour over chicken and celery mix.
Sprinkle chips over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken wings with salt and Accent.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Dip wings in beaten eggs.
Roll in cornstarch.
Brown wings in oil in skillet.
Drain on paper towels.
Place wings in baking dish.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add green chilies, soup and broth. Simmer 10 minutes.
No need to grease pan.
Layer the tortillas, chicken broth and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered. Serves 4 to 6.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Add sugar
to
water
and
let	come
to
a boil.
Make thickening of cornstarch and lemon juice; if not enough liquid add a
small
amount
of
cold water.
Add thickening to sugar syrup and boil 3 minutes.
Add beaten egg yolk (a small amount of lemon mixture
should
be
added to yolk first), but do not let cook. Cool,
then
pour
into a 9-inch baked pastry shell and cover with meringue.
Bake meringue in warm oven.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine Ragu and cooked ground beef.
Spread 1 cup of the Ragu/meat mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer 1/3 each of noodles, cottage cheese/yogurt mixture, Mozzarella, Ragu/meat mixture and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat twice.
Pour water in sides of pan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine corn meal and flour in bowl.
Add onion and squash; mix well.
Stir in egg and enough milk to make a stiff batter. Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep fat.
Fry until brown on all sides.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mushroom ragout
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp olive oil, add diced onion, cook until golden. Remove onion, set aside.
In the same pan heat 1 Tbsp olive oil and add freshly cut mushrooms.
Cook until they begin to release juices.

Return the onions, along with 2 cloves finely chopped garlic, 1 tsp freshly chopped rosemary, salt and pepper to taste. Cook until the mushrooms begin to brown about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in 1 Tbsp tomato paste, cook stirring constantly.
Add 1 1/2 cups chicken stock, simmer for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat. Stir in to form a sauce by adding 2 Tbsp cold butter and 1 1/2 tsp balsamic vinegar.
Garnish with freshly cut parsley and Parmesan cheese.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all together and bake in muffin tins until brown at 425°.

title: chicken primavera salad
directions: Cook rotini, drain and add meats and vegetables.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°. In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt and melted butter.
Stir in eggs, chiles, cottage cheese and Jack cheese.
Pour evenly into greased pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until firm and lightly brown. Cut into thin wedges.
Makes 16 to 18 pieces.

title: open face lemon pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, flour, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs.
Turn into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: con queso dip
directions: Brown onions and melt cheese in onions.
Pour in the tomatoes and chilies.
Serve this with nacho chips.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli.
Place in bowl.
Add bacon, cooked and crumbled.
Add sunflower seeds, raisins and red onions.
Toss well.
Stir in dressing.

title: quick pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in gallon jar. Shake to dissolve sugar and refrigerate.
Will keep for 2 months.

title: spam burger
directions: Grate Spam, cheese and onion.
Make into a ball.
Bake in oven on bottom of hamburger bun.
Butter the top half and place on cookie sheet, buttered side up.
Brown until cheese is melted.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine meat loaf ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chunky chocolate cookie squares
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Slowly beat in corn syrup, then egg and vanilla. Beat in flour mixture until blended.
Stir in pecans and half the chocolate.
Spread evenly in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes.
This makes a big pan of beans.

title: diet vegetable salad
directions: Mix together at least 24 hours before serving. Contains 70 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: oven baked vidalia onions
directions: Remove the skins from the onions.
Place in deep dish.
Melt butter.
Pour butter over onions.
Crush garlic and sprinkle over onions.
Sprinkle garlic powder over onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover tightly with tinfoil.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cub cakes
directions: Note: For furry paws, mix the frosting with grated coconut.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange, apple and celery.
Mix with sugar; let stand 15 minutes.
Prepare Jell-O according to directions on package, using only 1 cup water.
Let cool.
Add to fruit mixture. Refrigerate.

title: fruit punch
directions: Let all ingredients get cold before serving.
Make an ice ring out of some of the lemonade, a few cherries and cut-up oranges. Serves 100.

title: baklava (greek pastry)
directions: Combine walnuts, spice and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Melt butter.
Brush bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with melted butter. Place 1 pastry sheet in bottom of pan.
Brush with melted butter. Repeat this process 8 times.
Place one half of the mixture on top of the 8th sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Place two sheets on top of mixture, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Sprinkle on the rest of the mixture.
Brush with melted butter.
Place 8 more pastry sheets on mixture, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 300° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
When done baking, remove from oven and pour syrup.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Beat all ingredients.
Pour over cubed bread and sausage.
Chill overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix jello and begin to let jell.
Mix rice with partially set jello.
Mix pineapple, nuts and Dream Whip.
Stir well before serving.

title: salted almonds
directions: Shell almonds; blanch in boiling water.
Remove skins.
Brown lightly in butter.
Drain on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: microwave zucchini squash
directions: Allow 3 pounds winter squash to serve 4 people.
Pierce each squash twice.
Microwave on High allowing 8 to 11 minutes for 1 acorn and 13 to 16 minutes for 2 acorns, rearranging once.
When tender, let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Cut each in half.
Discard seeds.
Spoon out squash, mash and serve.
Season to taste.

title: butter gravy
directions: Melt butter in frying pan, then add flour until it comes to a browning substance.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Be sure before you put milk in, it is brown.
Also be sure you have a lot of biscuits.

title: oriental salad
directions: Brown almonds and sesame seeds in butter.
When brown, add seasoning packages from noodle packages.
Toss with cabbage and onions.
Place in covered dish and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Marinate overnight the dry mustard and vinegar.
In double boiler mix eggs and sugar with marinade.
Cook until custard thickens.
Cool.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Can be used with cold cuts, any meat, chicken, potato chips, vegetables, sandwiches, hot dogs, etc.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Slice zucchini and onion.
Put in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fish chowder
directions: Simmer the haddock, potatoes and onions in water.
Drain, reserve 1 cup.
Add milk, salt and pepper; heat.
Do not let boil. In a separate pan, melt the butter and add the flour.
Add to the chowder to thicken.

title: southern caviar
directions: Combine peas, peppers, onion and garlic.
In separate bowl, whisk together vinegar, oil and mustard; pour over bean mixture. Season with tabasco, salt and pepper.
Mash bean mixture slightly; refrigerate until ready to serve.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: creamy chicken on corn muffins
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat until crisp, about 4 minutes.
Pour off all but 2 teaspoons drippings. Add white sauce directly from packet and stir into drippings until smooth and pasty.
Stir in remaining ingredients except muffins. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and simmer, uncovered, 2 to 4 minutes until hot and thickened.
Meanwhile, toast muffins.
Top with chicken mixture.

title: pecan cups
directions: Blend
together softened cream cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, blending by hand.
Chill.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls; place
in	miniature
muffin pans (1 3/4-inch).
Press dough firmly to bottom and sides.

title: crock-pot bean sausage soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover with water.
Stir.
Cook on high for 8 hours.
Season to taste.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining dry ingredients, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: spanish beef salad
directions: Cut roast beef into long, narrow strips.
Marinate in dressing for 1 hour.
Toss in salad bowl with lettuce and additional dressing.
Border bowl with alternate slices of tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Serves 6.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Butter and flour a 9 x 10-inch glass pan.
Layer half the chilies on the bottom.
Top with half of the cheese and dot with butter; sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over it.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Just before cooking, beat eggs until frothy and add milk.
Pour over the chilies and cheese, lifting them gently to allow eggs to circulate.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 45 minutes or until the eggs are set at 350°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add last 3 ingredients to first 2. Mix together.
Chill before serving.

title: stack-up vegetable or seven layer salad
directions: In a 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, pepper, corn, zucchini, tomatoes and celery.
Spread mayo or other dressing over celery.
Seal edges of bowl tightly with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Combine with cheese and stir to partially melt cheese.
Add a dash of cayenne pepper.
Add Bisquick mix.
Stir to combine and form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Measure popped 3-minute popcorn into buttered bowl (4-quart or larger).
Combine together in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan the sugar, water, corn syrup, salt and vinegar.
Stir over heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cover; bring to a boil and let boil briskly for 3 minutes.
Uncover; insert candy thermometer and cook mixture to hard ball stage (260°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour slowly over popped corn, stirring with large, buttered spoon to coat each kernel.
Immediately form into balls.

title: oatmeal nut waffles
directions: Combine in a mixing bowl the wheat flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk, eggs, margarine and honey and beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Bake in a preheated, lightly oiled waffle iron about 5 minutes or until done.
Yields 12 to 14 waffles.

title: seafood casserole(for a crowd)
directions: Thoroughly mix first 10 ingredients in large container. Divide into two 3-quart casserole dishes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of each casserole.
Melt butter and drizzle over bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown in moderate oven (350°). May be garnished with parsley sprigs and lemon slices.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread; spread with butter on one side and arrange the bread, butter side down, in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese evenly over bread. Distribute green peppers (remove seeds) opened, evenly over cheese layer.
Sprinkle Monterey Jack cheese over peppers.
Beat eggs, milk, paprika, salt, oregano, pepper, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and chilies.
Chill overnight.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: *Other nuts may be substituted.

title: fried eggplant with garlic
directions: Skin the garlic and chop it.
Wash the eggplants and cut into serving pieces with one side of each round.
Heating peanut oil to medium heat, put the eggplants in.
Deep fry eggplants and scoop them out as soon as the skins slightly change color and drain oil. Add 2 tablespoons oil to the pot; saute chopped garlic.
Add eggplant and season with salt.
Stir in wine; mix well with soy sauce.
Stir-fry quickly and place in a platter.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Slowly add the milk.
Cook in the double boiler, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add egg yolks and cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove from the heat and add the butter.
When cool, add the vanilla extract, then pour the mixture into a baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue or whipped cream.

title: rhubarb strawberry crumbs(serves 6 to 8)
directions: I use 3 cups of rhubarb and 3 cups of strawberries (fresh or frozen).

title: apple pecan delight
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 13 greased pan. Pour brown sugar over pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix over sugar. Put cut up sticks of margarine onto cake mix. Spread pecans over margarine. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Boil lard, sugar, salt and water until dissolved.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and make sure it is completely dissolved. Add eggs and make sure the eggs are room temperature.
Then add flour, 2 cups at a time until the dough doesn't stick to hands. Let set in bowl for half an hour.
Then grease cookie sheet and make into roll and set another 1/2 hour.
Make sure to cover the rolls when they set.
No breeze should blow on them.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 45 rolls.
From start to finish takes about 2 hours.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: *If desired, add 1 pound browned ground beef to spaghetti sauce.

title: chocolate frosting for angel food cake elegante
directions: Mix ingredients all together and set in refrigerator for an hour. Then beat until thick and spread on angel food cake. Include the center area of cake. Slice with serrated knife.

title: spaghetti alla carbonara
directions: Cream butter by beating it against sides of bowl with wooden spoon until it is soft and fluffy.
Beat eggs and yolks until well blended; then stir in 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Heat large ovenproof bowl in 200° oven.
Bring 6 to 8 quarts water and salt to boil; add spaghetti and cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, for 7 to 12 minutes.
Fry bacon in skillet over moderate heat until crisp. Pour off half of bacon fat and stir into pan the red pepper, then the cream.
Bring cream to simmer and keep it warm until spaghetti is done.
When spaghetti is cooked and drained, transfer to heated serving bowl and stir in creamed butter, tossing and turning with fork to coat every strand.
Stir in hot bacon and cream mixture and finally, the beaten eggs and cheese, mixing everything together. Taste and season with salt and a few grindings of pepper.
Serve with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese at table.

title: pastry for 2 (9-inch) pie shells
directions: Mix and sift
dry
ingredients.
Add fat and mix deftly with fingers or	blender until fat particles are size of small peas. Sprinkle the
water,
a
tablespoon
at
a time, over a portion of the
mixture
while
tossing lightly.
Mixture will cling together when
pressed lightly with finger.	Divide into 2 portions.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Combine the 2 cups of water with the vanilla pudding and pie filling.
Also add the Jell-O peach gelatin mix in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Pour into bowl and chill well.
Blend in 2 cups prepared Dream Whip whipped topping.
Fold in diced peaches.
Spoon into cooled, baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with peach slices.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread on baking sheet or 2 pizza pans. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and add topping.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Mix both kinds of corn; stir in flour, eggs, salt, pepper and milk into casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned on top.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Mix ingredients and add salad dressing.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: brandied chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken.
Dip in flour and brown slowly in electric frypan in small amount of oil.
Combine melted orange juice and spices; pour over chicken.
Add brandy and simmer slowly or until chicken is tender.
Add water or more brandy if needed. Serve over rice.

title: mexican rice hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Top with cheese. Cover and bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Put on lower temperature if necessary to keep from burning.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Cook peppers, sugar and vinegar until mixture comes to a full rolling boil. Cook 1 minute more, stirring to prevent its boiling over. Remove from heat and add pectin, stirring it in well. Let set for 5 minutes. Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Add green or red food coloring, if desired. Makes 6 pints.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saut onion and celery in butter. Add flour, milk, mayonnaise, ketchup, bread crumbs, wine, lemon juice, parsley and other seasonings. Stir in crab meat and mix well. Mixture can be put in individual shells or casserole. Put a few bread crumbs on top and dot with a little butter. Heat at 375° until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: dip with crackers
directions: Put Saran Wrap into mold.
Press crabmeat into cream cheese in mold.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen holiday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into ice cube trays.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, take freezer tray out of freezer and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt margarine and crumble cookies.
Pat in pan (12 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 15 minutes or so at 350°.

title: veal schnitzel
directions: Fry the bacon to desired crispness; drain most of fat from pan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter.
Season veal with salt and pepper to taste.
When butter has melted, add veal and brown quickly on both sides.
Remove veal to warm platter.
Add lemon zest and heavy cream to pan; deglaze pan and pour over veal.
Serve with the bacon strips.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together to make crumbly topping.
Place evenly on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon asparagus tart
directions: In a saucepan, bring 1 inch of water to a boil.
Place asparagus in a steamer basket over water; cover and steam for 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet, saute onion and red or yellow pepper until tender; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, mayonnaise, flour, eggs, cream, dill, basil and pepper.
Fold in the salmon, asparagus, onion mixture and Swiss cheese.
Transfer to a greased 9 inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, garlic and sugar. Cook 20 minutes.
Mix onion, cream cheese and sour cream.
Place in casserole dish a layer of noodles and layer of meat mixture. Add layer of cream cheese and sauce last.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and flour and spread on pizza pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned, then cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust and refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients then fold in blueberries.
Grease a Bundt pan and dust with sugar.
Bake cake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: 7 layer salad(lo-cal recipe)
directions: Finely tear lettuce or spinach to form first layer.
Layer in order and top with mayonnaise mixture in a square, shallow dish. Make and store in fridge for quick meals or lo-cal snack.
Place toothpicks to keep plastic off top layer.
Slice in squares and serve with a spatula.
Great summer treat or any season.

title: dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pack cucumbers in jars, adding dill seed and garlic powder.
Fill jars with vinegar mixture.
Let set 10 to 14 days, then eat.

title: orange spice tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store tightly covered. Use 3 teaspoons of mix for each cup of boiling water.
One-third cup mix makes 1 quart of tea.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain and wash hamburger meat.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: curried cashews(a subtle change on good ole cashews)
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a frying pan.
Add cashews and curry powder and saute until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.

title: crab mold
directions: Mix gelatine and 2 tablespoons water.
Add to mushroom soup. Cook over low heat and stir.
Add cream cheese and crab.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and put in mold.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: oven fried steak
directions: Use enough cube steak for your family.
Dip steak in flour, pepper and salt to taste.
Then brown quickly in oil on both sides and place in baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water and steak sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn off oven and let stand for 30 minutes.
It's very moist and tender.

title: charoset
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the wine, then add the wine and mix thoroughly.
Makes 3/4 to 1 cup.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, Karo and Pet milk before cooking.
Start off cooking on high heat, stirring slowly.
When starts bubbling, lower heat to medium, stirring occasionally.
When it forms a soft ball in cold water, take off heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Put in sink in cold water.
Add pecans and start stirring.
Stir until it thickens enough to pour up in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut candy into pieces before it hardens!

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute minced onion, garlic and green pepper in oil. Add ground meat; brown lightly. Add tomatoes, olives and seasonings; simmer gently for 30 minutes. Add cheese and stir until just melted. Brown corn tortillas in hot oil.
Place 2/3 in a large casserole. Add meat mixture.
Top with remaining tortillas. Cover with 1 can tomato sauce. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cover with thick layer of grated cheese.
Melt. Serves 6.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add prepared vanilla
pudding.
Add
Cool
Whip on top when ready to eat.	Prepare this the day before serving.

title: cornmeal-fried catfish
directions: Heat oil (2 to 3 inches) in Dutch oven to 350°.
Rinse catfish and pat dry.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Mix cornmeal, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in milk, eggs, pepper sauce and 2 tablespoons vegetable oil until well blended.
Coat fish with cornmeal batter, shaking off any excess.
Fry fish until golden brown, turning once, if necessary.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 275° oven.

title: sugar cakes
directions: Cream oleo, eggs, vanilla and sugar together.
Gradually add milk, flour, baking soda and baking powder until all mixed together.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
In bowl, blend together soup, milk, mayonnaise, and mustard. Stir in cheese and tuna. Fold in macaroni. Turn into 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Mix breadcrumbs, butter, and paprika and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix spinach, mayonnaise, vegetable soup mix, sour cream and Accent.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours so that the soup absorbs the mixture.
Using a sharp knife, cut a circle around bread one inch from the outer edge to bottom crust.
(Do not puncture bottom.)
Slice center portion into squares.
Remove squares and cut each one in half horizontally (dipping size).
Pour dip into hollowed out bread.
When the cut bread is gone, break off sides of loaf for dipping.

title: sausage curry quiche
directions: Prepare single pie crust and refrigerate.
Cook sausage (chopped and crumbled) until brown and remove to a bowl.
Drain all fat from skillet.
Return 1 tablespoon and saute onions and celery 5 minutes.
Stir in curry.
Heat 2 to 3 minutes and return sausage mix and heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Put into chilled pie crust.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Combine cream cheese, vanilla and salt.
Work with your warm hands until it is creamed together.
Pinch and roll into tiny balls.
Drain cherries "very" well.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together. in the top of a double boiler while you wrap each ball around a cherry.
Dip each ball in chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: tropical apple salad
directions: In bowl, combine diced apple, sliced banana, sliced celery, broken walnuts and flaked coconut.
To prepare dressing, blend together mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Whip the cream; fold whipped cream into mayonnaise mixture.
Fold dressing into apple-banana mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate crescents the quick and easy way
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in bowl of mixer until blended.
Add cocoa alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Gradually fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until firm or freeze if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Beat eggs and sour cream; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over this and then crackers.
Pour melted butter over all of this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pink arctic freeze salad
directions: Soften cheese; add mayonnaise and sugar.
Combine with cranberries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into oblong or square plastic container.
Cover and freeze overnight.
To serve, cut into squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: To the thin white sauce, add the tomatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes with 1 slice of onion, then force through sieve.

title: instant hot cocoa(children's recipe)
directions: Mix all in large bowl.
Store in airtight jars or other containers.

title: easy oven omelet
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix any other ingredients together (precooked sausage, ham, green pepper, onion, cheese or whatever you like).
Stir in sour cream, milk, salt and eggs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
This is a nice dish to make ahead of time for a brunch.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a frying pan and cook until meat is brown and vegetables are soft. Reduce heat. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until well mixed and heated through. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Brush chicken with dressing. Sprinkle well with garlic powder and lemon pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour on soy sauce and bake 15 minutes more.
Use low-fat and no cholesterol dressing if watching calories.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Blend milk and lemonade together, then add Cool Whip.
Add enough red food coloring to make pink.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with cracker crumbs.
Chill.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk, butter, sugar and salt in pan; melt. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil mixture 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Beat in chocolate, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture in an 8-inch square pan.

title: fried ice cream
directions: You will need a clean empty vegetable can and tongs.

title: bar-b-q sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and cook 5 minutes before placing on meat.

title: tropical "julius"
directions: In blender, process yogurt and juices until smooth.
Add ice cubes to the 4-cup mark.
Process until smooth and creamy.

title: spicy chicken pasta salad
directions: The salad should be assembled just before serving, otherwise the melon will exude juice as it sits and the dressing won't cling as well.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle 1 package of Cheddar cheese over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Cook chicken in saucepan with water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper until tender.
Remove chicken and skim excess fat from broth.
To broth, add potatoes, carrots, onions, 1 tablespoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate-mint bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium-sized bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Set aside 2 cups of crumb mixture in small bowl; press remainder firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: orange carrots
directions: Slice carrots into thin rounds and cook until tender.
Drain. Mix sugar and flour.
Add orange juice.
Cook until thickened. Pour over carrot slices.
Add butter or margarine.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: maple pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Place cottage cheese, yogurt, pumpkin, flour, eggs, vanilla, maple syrup and spices into food processor.
Process until smooth, then pour the mixture into the crust using a rubber spatula to spread it evenly.
Place the pie in the middle of the oven and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Let it cool before serving. Store any leftovers in the refrigerator.

title: holiday squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar with fork.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder; mix until smooth. Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put mix into pan.
Cut 16 squares with knife.
Drop pie filling into center of squares (about 1 tablespoon).
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top when cool.

title: tuna delight
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk chicken or fish
directions: Season chicken as normal.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then flour in paper bag.

title: ma gillie's cranberry orange relish
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food chopper.
Add sugar. Mix well and chill in refrigerator several hours before serving. Makes 1 quart.

title: cracker barrel hot scratch biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening and moisten with milk.
Do not overmix.
Turn out on floured board, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out and bake in 450° oven until brown, about 12 minutes.

title: bonnie's dry butter beans
directions: Look beans over good. Rinse real good in cold water. Soak beans overnight. Pour off water. Cover with fresh water in large pot. Add the bacon, salt and pepper to taste. Add vegetable oil. Bring to a boil and cook on medium heat. Put lid on top of pot. Cook for 2 hours or until tender.

title: smoky chowder
directions: Brown salt pork in Dutch oven. Add onion and saute until transparent. Add potatoes and water to cover. Salt and pepper to taste and bay leaf.
Careful with salt as fish will add salt as well. Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer.
When potatoes are almost tender, add milk and fish and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until onion turns clear. Blend in flour well.
Pour in the milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt and red and black peppers.
Cook 5 minutes.
Carefully blend in crabmeat, trying not to break up. Place in lightly greased casserole or individual dishes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ida's chili
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Drain.
Add chili sauce.
Add pepper seeds, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 2 cans water. Simmer 3 to 5 hours.
Add extra water if necessary.

title: bacon-cheeseburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Remove and mix together with bacon pieces, breaking up any larger clumps with fork (or pastry mixer) until you have a fine mix.
Drain any excess grease and press into bottom of a deep-dish pie pan. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl and whip well. Pour mixture over beef crust and bake 40 to 45 minutes until top is browned and set.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before slicing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: mamma's toll house cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add soda, flour and salt, which have been mixed together.
Add hot water. Mix together until well blended.
Lastly, add nuts and chips. Flavor with vanilla; drop by half teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 150 cookies.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until well cooked.
Drain.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Use potato masher or mixer to blend.
Place back on heat and add salt and pepper.
Add butter and parsley flakes.
Pour into bowl and sprinkle with Hormel real bacon pieces.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to very hot for at least 15 minutes before you mix. Mix butter, sugar and egg until smooth.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together 4 times before stirring into butter mixture.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and add tomato sauce and spices; bring to boiling point and simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix together cottage cheese and egg.

title: deluxe au jus
directions: In a 2-cup measuring cup, dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Add all other ingredients and stir to blend.
Serve with steak, roast beef or other cuts of beef.
May also be used as a French dip.

title: jack's bologna sandwich
directions: Spread mayo evenly over bread.
Slice tomato and lay on top of bologna.
This makes my favorite sandwich.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add all together, except Cheez Whiz.
Top with Cheez Whiz. Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: frosty chocolate shake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ice in order listed in blender until smooth.
Add ice cubes 1 cup at a time, blending until smooth.
Serve.
Makes approximately 5 cups.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Press cookie dough into 12-inch greased pizza pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown.
Allow to cool in pan. Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in 2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread on cookie crust. Garnish with toppings as desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies.
Can half recipe if you like.
This is a great moist and chewy cookie.

title: sharon pound cake
directions: If you want chocolate cake, put 2 or 3 tablespoons of cocoa.

title: green beans almondine
directions: Over medium heat butter almonds with butter and simmer until golden.
Cook green beans (steam them).
Sprinkle them with lemon juice and almond mixture.

title: green beans with bacon and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon and crumble after removing from drippings; reserve 1 tablespoon.
Add oil; saut onion, garlic and green beans which have been broken into 3 or 4 pieces.
When green beans are tender-crisp or done to your liking, add bacon and tomatoes and heat through.
Add salt and pepper.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: matthew's hidden hot dog
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flatten rolls with hand.
They will be little triangles.
Place hot dot on triangle and wrap around hot dog.
Pinch the dough together so they stay wrapped.
Place on baking sheet, don't let them touch.
Bake for about 10 minutes.

title: beef broth
directions: Put beef bones or shank and water in a large stock pot. Simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours. Do not boil.
Strain.
Remove any meat from bones and save to use later in a soup.
Chill stock overnight.

title: fried wild turkey fingers
directions: Slice turkey breast into fingers 1/2-inch thick.
Mix eggs and milk and marinate fingers in mixture for 8 hours (in Ziploc bag).
Mix pancake mix and spices to taste.
Dredge fingers in breading.
Fry in hot oil 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until done.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in boiling, salted water until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Drain.
Place 1/2 onions in 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 cheese and 1/2 toast.
Repeat layer of onions and cheese.

title: gwen's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco,
margarine
and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate milk and flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple, then all other ingredients.
Pour in mold.

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine soup, oil, vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil for a few minutes.
Cool well before pouring over vegetables. Keeps well for several days in refrigerator.

title: six layer pineapple cake
directions: In large bowl, combine butter and sugar; let butter soften a little.
Mix well.
Add egg yellows and mix; then combine flour and milk until mix is creamy.
Grease and flour 9-inch round baking pans.
Spoon in 3 large spoonfuls of batter with "large" spoon.
Bake at 325° until cake is golden brown.
Layers will be thin.
This is a six layer cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all cheese. Form a ball. Roll in nuts. Serve with crackers or bread sticks.

title: dump stew
directions: Fill very large pot with water.
Put in spices; cover and bring to a boil.
Add onions and sausages and cook for 10 minutes. Add potatoes and cook for 10 minutes.
Add corn and cook for 10 minutes.
Add crabs and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes or until shrimp are done.
Pour off water and dump contents of pot into an oil cloth tablecloth.
Serve with butter, cocktail sauce and lots of napkins.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Stir together until blended, sugar, syrup and water. Boil rapidly until it spins 6-8 inch thread (242 degrees). When mixture begins to boil start beating egg whites until stiff enough to hold a peak. Pour hot syrup into egg whites, beating constantly. Mixture should stand in very stiff peaks. Blend in vanilla.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and salt and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Cook bacon in microwave and crumble (about 7 minutes).
Beat eggs with mixer; add onion salt and cheese.
Stir in green onion and bacon.
Add milk and blend well with mixer.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let sit about 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: clam dip with fritos
directions: Drain the clams (save the juice).
Mix all together, adding sauces to taste.
Refrigerate.
Add a little of the reserved clam juice to thin when serving with Fritos.

title: cornmeal pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Mix cornmeal, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine egg, pumpkin, milk and honey.
All at once, add to dry ingredients, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until it becomes clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool slightly and add strawberries.
Pour mixture into a baked pie shell or a graham shell.
Refrigerate and top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: "coon hunters cake"(make icing while cake is baking)
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Add icing while cake is hot.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables in large baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix other ingredients except crackers and butter.
Pour over vegetables. Crush crackers with melted oleo.
Put on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add onions and celery; saute until soft, but not brown. Stir in flour and blend until smooth.
Lower heat to simmer and stir in peanut butter.
Slowly add the chicken broth; bring to slow boil and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add half and half; heat soup just to boiling point.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve garnished with peanuts.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and vanilla and beat again. Add softened cream cheese and beat well.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each of 12 cupcake papers.
Fill cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before topping with pie filling.

title: spedina - small veal cutlets
directions: Dip veal cutlets into beaten eggs, then dip into Locatelli and bread crumb mixture.
Put aside. Mix eggs (chopped), Locatelli (grated), parsley, salt and pepper.

Lay out veal cutlets on foil. Place mixture of Locatelli, parsley and chopped eggs on cutlets. Take little pieces of butter and place that on the mixture. Roll up the cutlets and secure with toothpicks.
Brown cutlets in the broiler at 375° until brown on all sides.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with soda dissolved in water.
Add nuts and chopped apples.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: round steak louisiana
directions: Layer sweet potatoes, onion and green peppers in a large crock-pot.
Cut meat in 6 serving-size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and brown in hot oil.
Transfer meat to crock-pot.
Reserve drippings in skillet.
Cook garlic in reserved drippings until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour.
Add undrained tomatoes, beef broth, sugar, thyme, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; pour on meat and vegetables.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jumbles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients. Place jam in center.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Place broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend mushroom soup with cheese and pour over broccoli.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until sauce is bubbling.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 1 1/2-quart dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower with shrimp sauce
directions: Boil the cauliflower.
Boil shrimp.
Mix and simmer the shrimp soup, sour cream and a small amount of milk to thin mixture. Drain shrimp and add to soup mixture.
Pour over drained cauliflower.

title: basque mashed potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes and boil until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and blend in 2 tablespoons butter, broth and wine with a potato masher.
Additional hot water may be added for the desired consistency.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Butter a shallow serving dish; spoon in the potatoes and keep warm.
In a frying pan, quickly saute green pepper, onion and garlic in the remaining butter.
Do not brown.
Add the tomato and olive slices, warming through.
Make a well in the center of the potatoes for the vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Rinse and drain.
In skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add salt and tomato sauce. Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and noodles.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine
cukes	and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and let set for one hour.
Drain.
Place vinegar in saucepan with all ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: corn fritters
directions: Preheat oil at high.
Assemble blender.
Put egg yolks, half the corn and liquid in blender container.
Cover and process at liquefy until well blended.
Add half the dry ingredients and continue to process until well blended.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain well. Add cubed cheeses and chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Add the bottle of dressing and toss.
Allow to set for several hours or overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas, egg and sugar in a bowl.
Add melted butter, flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan or muffin tins.
Bake in oven at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ranchers chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Keep broth.
Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Add cut up chicken to onions and peppers.

title: swiss pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Bread pork chops with flour mixture. Heat oil in skillet and brown pork chops. Drain off oil. Top pork chops with onion slices and pour tomatoes over all. Reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine
dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once.
Knead
lightly
and roll out to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut out
and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 two-inch biscuits.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put eggs, oil, vanilla and carrots into blender container. Cover and use #5 speed, just until carrots are chopped.
Stop now and then and push carrots to bottom of container.
Add pecans. Use hold on button with quick on and off motions several times, until pecans are chopped.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Beat together flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, oleo, egg, milk and vanilla for 2 minutes and pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Drain peaches (reserve 3 tablespoons juice).
Dice into 1-inch pieces and place on batter.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add to eggs.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Grease and flour three 9-inch cake pans.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: triple chocolate kisses
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and extract on medium speed until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and beat on high to form stiff peaks.
Fold in grated chocolate.
Fill decorating tube with mixture; use large tip.
Pipe out quarter size circles on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Place a kiss on each circle.
Pipe meringue around kiss and cover completely.
Dust with cocoa.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mary's shrimp dip
directions: Wash and mash shrimp with pie blended. Mash eggs and cream cheese, blend all together. Stir in mayonnaise, onion, garlic salt, pepper and Tabasco to taste. Chill and let set overnight to blend flavors. Let it soften before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake in 10 x 13 greased cake pan at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Simmer cinnamon sticks and allspice in water for 5 minutes. Strain into mixture of cranberry and pineapple juices.
Add lemon juice, a little at a time, to suit taste.
Set mixture aside and heat to simmering temperature just before serving.
Makes 10 servings of 3/4 cup each.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together but pie crusts and pour in pie crust.
Chill and serve.

title: deer sausage balls
directions: Mix until thoroughly blended. Mixes better at room temperature. Make small balls and put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes on 325°.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, make into little balls.
Heat mushroom soup, bouillon cubes and water, bring to a boil, add meatballs.
Cook for 45 minutes, stir occasionally.
Add whipped sour cream, pour over cooked rice or noodles.

title: lamb roast(lammestek)
directions: Rub the roast with the butter mixed with the herbs.
Roast in hot oven at 375° for 1/2 hour.
Add the stock and baste every 15 minutes.
Add water, if necessary.
Roast for 2 hours or until done; use a thermometer.
Make gravy with drippings by adding 1 tablespoon cornstarch in a little water.
If you can get a butcher to bone a leg of lamb, stuff it with bread crumbs, chopped onion, chopped tomatoes, 2 beaten eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Roast the same way.

title: baking powder biscuits(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut margarine in with a blending fork or dough blender until fat is the size of small peas.
Add milk all at once; stir until dough is all mixed and forms a ball.
Roll out on a lightly floured board to a thickness of about 1/4-inch.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch round cutter.
If thicker biscuits are desired, roll out to a thickness of 1/2-inch and cut with a 2-inch cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on a baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: sinfully delicious italian love cake
directions: Pour cake mix into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Ricotta, sugar, vanilla and eggs in mixer for 5 minutes.
Spoon over prepared cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes and let cool.

title: pepperoni-ripe olive hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fold pepperoni slice in half and fold 2 more times to make triangle.
Stuff into olive.
Serve cold.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine cheese and butter, mix until well blended.
Add flour, red pepper and pecans and mix well.
roll into 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in oven of 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: upside-down strawberry shortcake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows evenly into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together, then sprinkle cheese on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and egg skillet
directions: In a skillet, saute potatoes in butter until tender and golden brown.
Add the onion and green pepper.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Add ham, eggs and cheese.
Cook until eggs are done.
Stirring occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and Karo.
Melt butter and add mixture.
Line pie shell with chopped pecans and pour mixture over them.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Mix together ground chuck, onion soup, egg, m.s.g. and bread crumbs.
Form into bite-size meat balls.
Arrange on cookie sheets.
Brown in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Stir together catsup and jelly until blended; heat over medium heat.
(I use crock-pot.)
Add meat balls.
Simmer until ready to use (at least 1 hour).

title: easy casserole
directions: Spread mixture over meat and mushrooms.
Bake in covered pan 3 hours in 300° oven.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate cherry creams
directions: Melt the chocolate chips and evaporated milk over low heat. Remove from heat.
Add and mix well the sugar, nuts and cherries. Chill mixture, then form in small balls.
Roll in coconut.
Chill 4 hours minimum.
Keep chilled until time to serve.

title: crawfish etouffee(kentucky style)
directions: Saute onion, peppers and garlic in margarine. Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: frikadeller (danish meat balls)
directions: Soak bread in milk until softened.
Beat eggs.
Add ground meat, salt, pepper, bread, flour and cloves.
Mix well.
Shape into patties against side of bowl with aid of a large spoon; fry slowly, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from pan and make gravy using drippings in pan.
Pour over frikadeller and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Put in bottom of casserole dish. Put eggs, peas and carrots over chicken. Combine soup and broth and pour over chicken. Mix flour and milk with fork until moistly smooth and pour over other ingredients. Pour butter over crust. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until crust is brown.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chickens.
Pour sauce over chickens and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Baste chickens as they cook.

title: stuffed chicken breasts italiano
directions: Slit lengthwise pocket in each breast, cutting 3/4 way through.
Combine Ricotta, olives, parsley, onion and garlic salt. Place 1/4 cup in each pocket.
Arrange stuffed breasts in 9 x 13-inch baking pan and cover with pasta sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and return to oven 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve on fettucine and garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: nappa cabbage turkey and orange salad
directions: Combine cabbage, orange, onion and turkey; in a salad bowl. Stir together hoisin sauce, vinegar and orange juice in a small cup; pour over salad and toss gently until well coated.
Makes 2 - 1/2 cup servings.

title: frozen banana pops
directions: Insert 8 wooden sticks or skewers into cut ends of bananas. Freeze until firm.
Melt together the chocolate and oil in small saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Cool slightly; pour into tall, narrow glasses.
Dip each frozen banana into chocolate mixture, coating evenly.
Immediately roll in Add-A-Crunch. Freeze.
For longer freezer storage, wrap securely in foil.
Makes 8 Frozen Banana Pops.

title: chicken in a brick
directions: Marinate chicken in garlic, lemon juice and olive oil.
Cook in covered skillet on medium heat; turn.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes and mash.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add corn meal and half and half; blend well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sweet potatoes, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted one inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Serve with scoop of whipped cream.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk and melted butter in a bowl. Stir until blended, then refrigerate for 30 minutes. Divide dough into 2 pieces. Roll out each piece to 1/8-inch thickness, about 8 x 10. Spread each rectangle with uncooked sausage and sprinkle on the peppers and onion. Then roll up lengthwise and place in freezer for an hour to make slicing easier.

title: mincemeat snack cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar.
Mix flour, soda and cocoa.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add mincemeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of cooking oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Simmer for 15 minutes; stir in sour cream and simmer 10 minutes more.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Boil butter, margarine and sugar mixture for 2 minutes. Grease cookie sheet.
Lay graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Place almonds on crackers.
Spoon butter mixture over crackers.
Bake at 325°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Whisk Egg Beaters with milk.
Skin the chicken and cut into nuggets.
Dip pieces in egg mixture, then roll in cornflakes.
Put coated nuggets on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serve with barbecue sauce, honey and mustard or fat-free Ranch dressing as dipping sauces.

title: venison chili
directions: Place oil in frying pan over medium heat and spread so it coats the surface.
Add ground meat and onion and cook until the meat is brown.
Stir often with a spatula to keep the meat from sticking to the pan.
Add rest of ingredients to the pan; stir. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll dough into balls and pat in lightly greased pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or longer.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, mix milk and confectioners sugar. Bring to rolling boil.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Turn off heat and blend in Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into small pieces.
Place in a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Mix the flour, sugar, salt and spices, then sift over the apples.
Pour cream over pie.
Top with strips of pastry.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Peel potato and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Combine soup/recipe mix, potato and corn (drained).
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, partially cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in half and half or milk plus 1 tablespoon butter or margarine. Heat through.
Do not boil!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sugar glazed walnuts
directions: Put butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and melt on High (about 1 minute) in microwave.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon. Microwave on High 2 minutes; mix well.
Add nuts and mix to coat. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread out onto wax paper and cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 1 pound.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Put sugar on apples; let stand about 10 minutes.
Melt butter; add to apples and sugar.
Add egg, flour, soda and spices; mix. Add nuts.
Bake for about 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: huddie's chocolate cake
directions: Melt butter in sheet pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar with 3 tablespoons of
cocoa and mix with self-rising flour; add milk and vanilla.
Pour in melted butter and pour in buttered pan.
In separate pan mix 2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup cocoa and boiling water.
Pour over cake in pan. Do not stir!
Cook about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, oatmeal and nuts. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and flatten.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water 24 hours.
Drain; rinse in cold water.
Let stand in cold water 3 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salt and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand until next morning.
Boil 35 minutes with spices to taste.
Put in jars and use hot water bath 10 minutes and take out to let seal.

title: dill pickles
directions: Add to each quart.
Pour over boiling brine; seal.
Can use after 6 weeks.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil in a large skillet.
Add fish; cover, reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove fish from skillet with a slotted spatula; set aside.

title: cream cheese burritos
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place ham on each tortilla.
Spread each tortilla with cream cheese mixture.
Roll, cover and chill with seam side down.
(This can be done up to 5 days in advance.) To serve, slice in 1/2-inch slices.
Do not freeze.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Blend well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° and then reduce to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until done.
I check with a toothpick in center.

title: summer salad
directions: Clean and shred lettuce.
Combine with onions and top with fruit.
Best if chilled prior to serving.
Apply dressing just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Melt chocolate and butter.
Set aside. In
large	bowl
mix
eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute. Add
chocolate
mix and beat until smooth.	Mix flour and
salt. Add
to
chocolate	mix.
Add
nuts
and chocolate chips.
Beat at	low
speed
or	by
hand just until flour is absorbed.	Do not overbeat.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain. Add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
While simmering, pop biscuits and press in greased (Pam) muffin pans.
Spread out over bottom and sides.
Scoop in sauce mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Enjoy.
Great for a sleepover.

title: new river chili (spicy)
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cook ground beef and onion and drain.
Add all together; simmer on low heat for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Yield: 2 quarts.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients together, then drain off excess grease.
Set aside.
Add all the ingredients except for cheese to the meat mixture.
Cook slowly about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Place 1/3 of the meat sauce into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of noodles, then a layer of cheese, more sauce, noodles and cheese.
Cover with remaining sauce and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove mushroom stems and reserve. Wash and dry caps, removing the spores. Brush with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Arrange in glass baking dish. Wash and dry the stems and mince. Put handfuls in corner of towel and twist to extract as much juice as possible. Saute stems with the scallions in 2 tablespoons melted butter for 4 to 5 minutes or until pieces begin to separate. Lower heat and add flour. Stir for 1 minute. Stir in cream and simmer for 1 minute or until thickened. Add parsley and dash of black pepper. Fill the mushroom caps with this mixture. (May be refrigerated overnight at this point.) Sprinkle each mushroom with grated cheese; dab a small amount of melted butter on top. Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until lightly brown. Worth the effort! Yield: 12 mushrooms.

title: bran muffins
directions: Place 3 cups Raisin Bran in Kitchen Aid mixer.
Blend.
Mix next 4 ingredients in a separate bowl.
Sift dry ingredients into Bran flakes.
Turn mixer on to blend dry ingredients.
Mix 1 egg, buttermilk and oil in Tupperware blender/shaker.
Shake well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Blend only until moist.
Add 1/2 to 3/4 cup raisins.
Pour into 12 muffin cups.
Fill to the top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Fry sausage and onion until lightly brown.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Place alternate layers of macaroni and sausage in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour balance of sauce over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: kyle's best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening and margarine until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix until blended.
Stir in flour, soda and salt, mixing until well blended.
Add nuts and chips. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: one cup fruit salad
directions: Thoroughly drain orange segments and pineapple chunks.
Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: pink delight
directions: Place pineapple in large saucepan; add jello and heat until jello dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and stir into jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cover pie shells with broken pecans.
Mix sugar, margarine, Karo syrup, vanilla and eggs.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook date loaf
directions: Chop dates, pecans and marshmallows.
Crush graham crackers. Knead together with milk in large bowl.
Shape into loaf and place on greased platter.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in icebox.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, milk and cocoa 1 minute. Add oats and vanilla. Beat 3 minutes. Drop on wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken approximately 45 minutes.
Dice chicken and put into a casserole dish.
Add dry stuffing mix.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in Marshmallow Creme, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir and leave in container to cool.
Cut and serve.

title: golden fruit nectar punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Pour chilled mixture into chilled punch bowl.
Add lemon juice, apricot nectar and frozen juice concentrates.
Stir until well combined.
Add ginger ale.
Top with scoops of sherbet; garnish with fresh mint leaves, if desired.

title: skillet eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Saute eggplant and onion in butter or margarine in large frying pan for 10 minutes or until barely tender.
Stir in tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper; cover.
Cook slowly over medium heat for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: angel food pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar in a sauce pan or top of double boiler.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly, cook until thick and clear (about 10-12 minutes).
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add 3 Tbsp. sugar and vanilla, beating until egg whites are creamy.
Pour hot cornstarch mixture slowly over whipped egg whites, beating continuously.
Cool slightly and fill pastry shell.
Cover with whipped cream and sprinkle grated chocolate over top.
Chill.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix everything together slowly and pour into pie shell.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix white sugar and cocoa together.
Add eggs (beaten).
Add vanilla, melted butter (or oleo), Pet milk and coconut.
Mix and put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Pecans can be substituted for coconut.
Serve with Cool Whip and cherry.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 3-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Freezes well.

title: ritz crackers
directions: Put it in oven and bake until cheese melts.

title: sawdust dough
