directions: Mix wallpaper paste with water to make a thin paste.
Add sawdust slowly to get a dough consistency.
Add a little salt as a preservative.
This dough will have a textured finish. Refrigerate overnight.
Objects will need to dry several days before they can be decorated or painted with tempera.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water in a saucepan over low heat until raisins are plump, 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisin liquid into measuring cup; add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham tortilla rolls(serves 15)
directions: Let cream cheese set out to soften.
Chop ham finely.
Mix all ingredients together and spread thin on flour tortillas.
Roll-up, cover and refrigerate for at least 3 to 4 hours, preferably overnight.
Slice in 1/2-inch rounds.
Serve with your favorite salsa on top.

title: "tot's" cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fry into small patties.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and melt butter; mix together.
Line a long pan with half of mixture.
Pat down firmly; set aside.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy; set aside.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Cover cucumber slices with water; add salt and let stand overnight.
Boil sugar and vinegar until it becomes thick.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning drain slices; wash and drain slices.
Pour sugar and vinegar mixture over slices.
Put in freezer boxes and freeze.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients, put in crock-pot and cook for 6 to 8 hours on low heat.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; add butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve hot, but can be served cold. Decorate with parsley and olives.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix together
the
cornmeal, salt, flour and soda.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes(company dish)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes.
Peel and mash with melted butter and salt.
Mix all together in 2 small or 1 large rectangular Pyrex dish.
Heat for serving, or freeze.
After freezing, reheat completely before adding marshmallows to top.
Lightly brown and serve.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy in large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Gradually beat flour mixture until well blended.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap; flatten lightly and refrigerate for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar and salt together.
Combine well beaten eggs, margarine and milk; mix well with corn mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir from the bottom 2 or 3 times during the first 30 minutes of baking time.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Saute onion with ground meat while it is browning; drain and add salt, pepper, corn and tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes. Add chili powder. Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Make a thin cornbread batter and spoon over the top.
Bake at 400° until cornbread is done on top.

title: saucy garden patch vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine soup, sour cream, milk, seasoned salt, vegetables, half of cheese and half can of onions.
Spoon into an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecued salmon
directions: In a small saucepan, heat butter, sugar and honey over medium heat until melted.
Add mustard, soy sauce, oil, ginger and/or garlic.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Measure marshmallows and butter into large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and popcorn.
Wet hands and shape into 2 1/2-inch balls.
Wrap in wax paper and store in loosely covered container.

title: citrus cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl mix all cake ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until it tests done.
While cake bakes, combine ingredients for frosting.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: In a medium bowl, put margarine, brown sugar and Karo syrup. Put in microwave and cook for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Cook again for 3 minutes.
Take out of microwave and add baking soda. Mix well. Put popped corn in large bowl and pour mixture over popcorn.
Mix well.

title: orange pineapple cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges with juice in mixer bowl.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Take 18 slices of bread and cut off the crusts.
Make 9 sandwiches and cut into 4 pieces.
Makes 36.

title: icebox cake
directions: Squeeze juice from the lemons.
Mix lemon juice with Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Chill as for a pudding.

title: supper sandwich bake
directions: Spread six slices bread with butter.
Arrange in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Toast in moderate oven (350°) about 15 minutes.
Combine beef, ketchup and salt.
Spread over toast (1/3 cup per sandwich).
Top with frankfurters, cut almost in half lengthwise, onion and cheese slices.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over bread.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°), about 50 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add chocolate chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco mix.
Put in bottom of bowl.
Top with crushed chilies, then diced tomatoes, then with grated cheese (don't mix, leave in layers).
Serve with Doritos or nachos.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix in pan; sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Cool for 1 minute and add all other ingredients. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let harden.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat after each.
Add one cup flour at a time and beat after each cup.
Add soda to sour cream and stir.
Add to butter mixture; add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ground beef puff casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Press 5 sliced biscuits in bottom of dish; spread to form a bottom crust.

title: syl's single pastry crust
directions: Mix together oil and milk.
Add to flour.
Using a pastry blender or fork, work mixture into a soft dough.
Pie crusts made with oil are tender though not as flaky as those made with harder fats.
Place dough into a 9-inch pie pan and fill it with the desired filling.

title: beefy peach harvest
directions: Saute almonds in oil until slightly browned.
Add beef, peppers and onion.
Saute until beef is browned.
Add peaches, water, soy sauce and seasonings; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sorority casserole
directions: Brown turkey and sausage together.
Add mushrooms, celery, onion and green pepper and simmer until tender.
Pour off excess fat.
Add cheddar, sauce and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add pasta. Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8-10.

title: sweet floret salad
directions: In small saucepan, combine mayo, sugar, oil and vinegar. Bring to boil, whisking constantly.
Cool to room temperature. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add dressing.
Toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Add bacon.

title: 20 mile dessert
directions: Chop the peaches up.
Combine prepared pudding and chopped peaches.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt margarine; add marshmallows and melt together. Add vanilla and food coloring until well blended. Add corn flakes. Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper. Decorate with 3 cinnamon candies. Cool.

title: glazed vegetables
directions: Place all vegetables in a pot and cover with water.
Cook 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Put in 7 x 11-inch baking dish, vegetables and other ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fried rice
directions: Brown bacon.
Cook rice while bacon is frying.
Remove cooked bacon.
Drain half of bacon grease.
Saute green onions and mushrooms in leftover grease.
Push to side of pan.
Add eggs and scramble.
Crumble bacon.
Add to pan.
Stir.
Add cooked rice and soy sauce.
Season with garlic powder to taste.
Stir well. Simmer 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth. Fold in half of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Prepare pudding according to package directions using the 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
Can also substitute lemon or chocolate pudding.

title: minute fudge frosting(heart association)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla. Bring to a boil and simmer one minute.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
Use on Black Devil's Food Cake.

title: sweet potato pie(makes 3 pies)
directions: Mix on medium.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pampango frozen fruit salad
directions: Chill all fruits, dipped in syrup or juice to prevent discoloration or drying out.
When cold, drain all fruits.
Be careful to keep each piece of fruit in tact.
Set aside.
Fold in whipped cream into mayonnaise.
Carefully fold whipped mixture into fruits.
Arrange fruit salad in a bowl and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Fruit salad may be served as is, or freeze and then serve.
Serves 12.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and boil sugar and water.
When cool, add orange juice and pineapple juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and ice.
To make ahead of time, freeze the water, sugar and juice mixture. When ready to serve, thaw and just add ginger ale.

title: delicious orange cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Dissolve soda in sour cream; add to mixture alternately with flour and baking powder.
Add rind and nuts; mix by hand.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, mix juice of 2 oranges with 1 cup sugar; heat to dissolve sugar.
Pour over baked cake slowly.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt cheese. Add soup, sour cream and onion.
Mix well.
Pour a small amount of cheese mixture into chicken (enough to moisten chicken).
Place a spoonful of chicken on a flour tortilla.
Roll up and place in an ovenproof baking dish, seam side down.
Pour remaining cheese mixture over tortillas.
Bake at 400° until cheese is bubbly. Top with more chopped onion and sour cream.

title: single man's supper
directions: Locate your most recent telephone book.
Dial your choice of pizza delivery, Pizza Hut, Little Caesar's, etc.
Locate your remote control; sit back and channel surf while waiting for them to deliver.
Take a break to hunt through your pockets and gather spare change to come up with a tip for the poor delivery guy.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat halfway through.
Add onion, pepper, chili powder, taco mix, salt and pepper and garlic.
Add tomatoes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Add more taco seasoning to taste.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fabulous fruit
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve (bananas darken if not used pretty quickly).
Simple and delicious!

title: cobbler a la peach
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add melted Crisco and milk.
Mix until well blended.
In a saucepan, place the fruit with juice and the sugar. Bring to a boil.
Put the first mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour fruit mixture on top. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
(Batter will rise and make crust.)

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Work flour, sugar and margarine with your fingers into crumbs. Set aside 1 1/2 cups of crumbs for topping.
Mix water, molasses and baking soda together, then add to the remaining crumbs.
Mix until batter is very thin but still lumpy.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups crumbs that were set aside.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: diabetic pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together with whole milk, pour in mixer can and fill to the fill line with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and set aside.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add milk and lime juice.
Fold in half of egg whites and pour into baked pie shell.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
Serve hot with chips or as topping for baked potatoes, noodles or spaghetti.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. While still hot, stir with wooden spoon.
Cool and form into balls. Roll in granulated sugar.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: In a large baking dish, blend onion mix or golden herb with lemon, sour cream, mustard, lemon juice and water.
Add chicken; turn to coat.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Mix everything but Ritz crackers.
Make balls with mixture. Roll balls in crushed Ritz crackers.
Makes 24 small balls (hors d'oeuvre).

title: familia
directions: Soak in fruit juice overnight.
Variety is all but endless varying fruits, nuts and juices. Makes 10 servings.
Each serving contains 167 calories and 9.92 grams fat.

title: barbecue cocktail smokies
directions: Saute onion. Add lemon juice and brown sugar. Cook until sugar dissolves. Add chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce and barbecue sauce. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Add cocktail smokies, bring to a boil; and let simmer until heated through.

title: baked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place cleaned turkey in roaster pan. Salt and pepper turkey inside and out.
Margarine may be basted on turkey to taste.

Pour all water into pan with turkey and cover. Place covered pan in preheated oven and cook at 500° for 1 hour. At end of 1 hour, turn off oven but leave turkey in unopened oven for approximately 8 hours.
Be sure to leave oven closed for entire time.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and oil.
Next add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: baked spareribs with dressing
directions: Boil spareribs until tender.
Pour broth over bread crumbs. Add salt, pepper, eggs, butter and celery.
Place ribs into roasting pan.
Spread dressing around ribs and bake until brown at 350°.
Bake and serve in same dish.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower and water in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover with glass lid.
Microwave 9 minutes on High.
Drain. Combine mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt in small mixing bowl. Spoon mustard sauce on top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: holiday wassail
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, combine cider, lemon juice and sugar. Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
In a spice bag, place cinnamon and cloves in the center of a double-thick 6-inch square of 100% cotton cheesecloth.
Tie closed with a clean string.
Add spice bag and sliced oranges to the cider mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag and oranges and discard.
Serve cider in mugs.
Makes approximately 16 servings.

title: old-fashion cream pie
directions: Mix together flour, salt and sugar, then add whipping cream, half and half and oleo.
Cook until it starts to thicken, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry de "lite" trifle
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, break up angel food cake in small pieces. Mix pudding with 2 cups skim milk.
Add frozen yogurt to pudding. Pour over cake and set in refrigerator approximately 1/2 hour. Mix 2 packages jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries. Pour over top of cake.
Refrigerate overnight or until set. Serves 16.

title: rio grande fried onion rings(makes 8 servings)
directions: In medium size bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, the paprika, salt and baking powder.
With wire whisk, stir in beer until batter is fairly smooth.
Set batter aside.
Meanwhile, cut onions across into 1/3-inch thick slices; separate into rings.
In plastic food storage bag, place remaining 3/4 cup flour.

title: harvest pumpkin fudge
directions: Prepare a 9 x 9-inch pan lined with aluminum foil.

title: banana split
directions: Melt butter; add to graham cracker crumbs and mix.
Spread crumbs on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice bananas in circles.
Lay bananas over crumbs.
Add lemon juice to condensed milk; stir and pour over bananas.
Drain pineapple and spread over condensed milk.
Spread whipped cream over pineapple.

title: asparagus delight
directions: Drain asparagus.
In casserole dish put a layer of asparagus, mushroom soup and egg slices.
Sprinkle with half the peanuts and cheese.
Repeat layers and end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole bubbles.
Green beans may be used instead of asparagus.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Beat thoroughly and bake on an aluminum griddle to save fat.

title: ground beef meal-in-one
directions: All ingredients are optional except ground beef.
You can put anything on it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish and put chicken in the bottom.
Pour drained LeSueur peas on top, then cover with rice.
Heat milk and soup and pour over rice.
Use a fork to separate rice and allow sauce through.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Put in cubed bread, then grated cheese, then browned sausage (drained).
Beat eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk and mustard.
Pour on and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Before baking, pour on mushroom soup diluted with 1/2 cup milk and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: guilt free chocolate mousse
directions: Combine pudding and milk. Refrigerate for 10 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt butter, water and cocoa; bring to a boil, then set aside to cool.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, soda, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Combine all together.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake in a 17 x 11-inch greased and floured cookie sheet (3/4-inch deep) for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice in shroom sauce
directions: Mix soup, water and onion soup in saucepan and heat over medium heat until hot.
Spray casserole dish with Pam or use a small amount of Crisco to grease pan. Spread Minute rice (uncooked) on the bottom of the casserole dish.
Place chicken on rice.
Pour hot mixture over chicken and rice.
Make sure all of the rice is moistened.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: my favorite salad
directions: Toss everything together in a large bowl and enjoy.
Unusual items can be found at "The Staff of Life" in Woolwich.
The French cured herbs can also be used in soup, pasta, dips, etc.

title: cider-hot mulled
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and place on stove.
Heat slowly and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Refrigerate any leftover.
Always serve cider hot.
Serves about 12.

title: chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; shred or dice and set aside.
In a casserole dish, pour soups (undiluted) and 1 can water; mix well.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice; mix well.
Place chicken in soup and rice mixture. Cut up butter and place on chicken and rice mixture.
Place in 350° oven and cook 1 hour, uncovered.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Steam broccoli slightly; cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Toss with mayonnaise.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla and beat well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine. Reserve 1/2 cup of crumb mixture. Press remaining crumb mixture onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat cream cheese and remaining 1 cup of sugar with electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs, sour cream and lemon juice. Beat until well blended. pour over crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until just set. Cool in oven with door ajar for 30 minutes. Cool completely on rack. Refrigerate after cool for 4 hours or overnight.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Roll dough out in about 1-inch balls.
Place them on a sprayed cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cookie crumb crust
directions: Combine the crumbs with
sugar
and melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Press the mixture
firmly
against
the sides and bottom of pie pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 400° and cool.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until the rice is tender.
Stir occasionally during the last half hour of baking.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: baked squash
directions: Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until well set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine and dip each slice of bread into it.
Stack and slice through into triangles.
Scal milk and add beaten eggs and sugar.
Add milk and raisins.
Place bread in flat baking dish and pour liquid over all.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place pudding dish in another pan with hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a very delicious pudding.

title: pumpkin gingersnap pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin and pumpkin pie spice.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand about 10 minutes to soften before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Pour in 2-quart baking dish.
Cook and stir crumbs in butter in small skillet until browned.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in a large bowl. Add desired amount of salt and pepper. Pound chicken breasts to tenderize and soften. Put chicken into bowl. Rub the wet ingredients into the chicken. Cover and keep marinated in the refrigerator for up to 5 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a baking dish, combine rice, chicken, mushroom or celery soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: meat loaf with quick oats
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients thoroughly with 1 can tomato sauce. Pack firmly in 8 x 4 x 3-inch pan.
Chill about 1 hour.
Unmold into a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake 20 minutes more.

title: russian fluff hot dish
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Cut bacon into small pieces; brown and drain.
Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Mix bacon, onion and ground beef together.
Cook celery slightly; then add celery, undrained peas, soup, undrained mushrooms and green pepper to hamburger mixture.
Add cooked Rice-A-Roni and bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickle relish
directions: Soak chopped vegetables in 1/3 cup salt and cover with 3 trays of ice for 3 hours.
Drain off juice.
Bring all other ingredients to boil, then put in vegetable mixture and bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: spiced pears in rum raisin syrup
directions: Prepare home canning jars and lids.
Peel, halve and core pears.
Place in soaking solution to prevent darkening.
Peel pineapple; remove eyes from pineapple and cut into tidbits. Measure 2 cups pineapple tidbits and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large saucepan, except rum.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse pears.
Poach pears in water for about 5 minutes, cooking 1 layer at a time.
Pack pears in hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove from heat and stir reserved pineapple tidbits and rum into syrup.
Carefully spoon syrup over pears, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Add a cinnamon stick to each jar.
Remove air bubbles with nonmetallic spatula.
Adjust caps. Process 25 minutes in a boiling water bath canner.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add baking soda to soup; add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Add flour and spices; stir.
Add nuts and raisins.
Makes 1 large loaf.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out dry.
Frost if you wish.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave until almost melted.
Mix with cream of coconut with a whisk until smooth.
Can add rum or rum flavoring to taste.
Serve with chunks of fresh pineapple, melon, grapes, strawberries, etc.

title: fudge marble squares
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar until blended.
Add egg. Melt unsweetened chocolate with butter, margarine and water.
Stir flour and sugar together.
Add 2 eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Drop cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter and swirl with a knife. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, a little water, bay leaves, paprika, poultry seasoning, oregano, cayenne, parsley flakes, dry mustard and salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer as long as possible.
Add 1 tablespoon vinegar and 2 tablespoons brown sugar after cooking 1 hour.

title: asparagus and crab quiche
directions: Place the asparagus tips on the bottom of the pie crust and cover with the shredded crab meat.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together and pour mixture over the crab and asparagus.
Place pie on baking sheet and cook for about 30 minutes until the top is brown. Serve lukewarm.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Save egg whites for cream filling.
Sift ingredients into a bowl.
Add other ingredients all at once.
Mix until smooth.
Drop teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (preheated).

title: moist-jam cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and mix with all other ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake at 350° until done.
Cool and frost with Jam Cake Icing.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Combine olive oil, garlic, onion, red pepper, oregano and Italian seasoning. Saute, stirring often, until onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, (stir occasionally) for about 1 hour. Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: coffee cake(frozen bread dough)
directions: Defrost dough and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Melt butter.
Mix together sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
When bread is doubled in bulk, grease a 10-inch ring form pan well with some of the melted butter.
(Can use 9 x 13-inch pan.)
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan, then sprinkle about 4 tablespoons of the sugar-cinnamon mixture over nuts.
Cut dough into 2-inch balls (golf ball); roll up and dip balls in melted butter, then roll in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Place balls in layers on bottom of pan. Drizzle leftover butter-sugar cinnamon on top.
Let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool 5 minutes and slide out of pan.

title: spiders
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter; stir until all melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles, raisins, or marshmallows and Rice Krispies or nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper and cool.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and cut up into pieces.
Layer in pan chicken, 6 tortillas and sauce and cheese mixed together.
Repeat and top with grated cheese and black olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables a few minutes.
Combine soup, cheese and mushrooms and pour over vegetables in a casserole dish.
Pour onion rings on top.
Bake between 325° and 350° until hot.

title: eggless cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Add the milk, then the fruit and lastly, the flour, salt, baking powder and spices sifted together.
Turn into a greased pan and bake in a slow oven about one hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in jam, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, salt, soda and seasonings alternately with buttermilk. Mix well after each addition. If desired, fold in 1 cup flaked coconut.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and glaze with Brown Sugar Glaze.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into balls. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 20 to 25 balls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple with juice.
Mix well.
Put in individual molds or a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Congeal.
Garnish with a small dab of mayonnaise.
Serves 8.

title: aunt laura's lime pickles
directions: Cut cukes in chunks or thick slices.
Combine water and lime. Cover cukes.
Soak 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and wash with clean water.
Cover with fresh water and let stand 3 hours.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and 1 cup juice from fruits. Set aside until it begins to set.
Add the fruits and marshmallows.
Pour into long Pyrex dish and let set.

title: punch
directions: Mix Southern Comfort, cranberry cocktail, orange juice and lemonade.
Fill the rest up with 7-Up.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, flavorings and 7-Up.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brunswick stew
directions: In Dutch oven or large pot, place all meat; cover with water. Cook, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Strain stock into another pot and refrigerate long enough to remove fat from stock.
Remove meat from bones and dice; set aside.
After skimming fat from broth, add tomato sauce, hot pepper sauce, vinegar, sugar, onion, garlic and tomatoes.
Simmer about 45 minutes.
Add corn and meat.
Simmer another 15 minutes and stir in bread crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yield: 6 quarts.
Freezes good in plastic jars.

title: yuletide drops
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in sour cream.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves. Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in oats, nuts, dates, raisins and chopped cherries.
Drop from rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with a halved cherry.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet.
Cool on rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: devan's cabbage & smokies
directions: Cut up cabbage and place in bag.
Add a row of butter pats. Add chopped onions, then add another row of butter.
Add little smokies and mushrooms and rest of butter.
Cook at 425 degrees for about 45 minutes.
Add meat tenderizer for flavor.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Line muffin tins with cupcake liners.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except pie filling, and fill each cup 2/3 full of cheese mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with pie filling.
Makes 24.

title: pickled salad
directions: Cut carrots, cauliflower and zucchini in 1-inch chunks; blanch 3 to 4 minutes.
Put piece of apple and some chopped parsley in each jar.
Add 5 cucumbers, 4 tomatoes, pieces of cauliflower, pieces of carrot and zucchini, 5 onions, 1 clove garlic, pieces of pepper and pieces of celery.
Fill to 1/2 inch from top.
On top, put chopped parsley and 1 bay leaf.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Prepare strawberries; set aside.
Combine in saucepan the sugar or Sweet 'N Low and cornstarch; mix together. Add water.
Cook over low heat until thickened (may add red food coloring and, also, juice of lemon).
When thickened, add the strawberries and pour in baked pie shell.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: stir fry vegetables
directions: Add oil to hot wok or large skillet, add vegetables, and stir fry until crisp tender. Season to taste.

title: muscadine grape jelly
directions: Put juice and Sure-Jell in large boiler.
(Must be no more than 1/3 full.)
Bring to a full boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in sugar at once and boil hard for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and put in jars.

title: quick punch
directions: Scoop lime sherbet into punch bowl.
Add lemon-lime carbonated beverage, pouring liquid slowly down the side of the bowl.
Ladle into punch cups.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Blend shortening and margarine together.
Add sugar slowly; beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well.
Sift flour and soda together and add alternately with buttermilk, starting and ending with flour.
Add coconut to cake batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cake will fall, but don't worry.

title: mama's buttermilk pie
directions: Break eggs in a dish with melted butter; add sugar, then sift the flour on the sugar and beat together well.
Then add vanilla and buttermilk.
Bake in one crust in moderate oven for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°.
Be careful not to burn, just a lovely brown. This is an old Virginia recipe.

title: banana yogurt muffins (low-fat)
directions: Use muffin tin liners.
Fill and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Add ingredients together.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch bread pans and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 loaves.

title: striped chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Heat 1/2 cup peanut butter and butter until smooth.
Stir in crumbs.
Cool.
Press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Chill.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: On a plate, layer as follows:

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, jello, water and oil in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add strawberries.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Layer sliced potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan. Add onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over potatoes and bake until tender.
Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: cheese-pepper snacks
directions: Mix first six ingredients, and spread over unrolled crescent dough. Do not cut the dough on the perforations. Roll up and cut into slices about 1/4 inch thick. Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: bean chowder
directions: Cook beans separately until nearly done.
Cook beef and chopped onions and peppers together until nearly done, drain. Pour tomato sauce with remaining ingredients in pan with meat mixture and simmer about 15 minutes.
Then mix meat mixture with beans in large pot.
Simmer for 3 to 6 hours.
Stir often and add water as needed.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate, sugar and butter in a saucepan.
Heat very slowly, then set aside to cool.
(Do not boil.)
Whip one egg at a time into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in 3-inch strips 1/3-inch wide.
Brown beef and garlic, add soy sauce and water.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Add vegetables.
Drain tomatoes, add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Add juice to cornstarch; blend well.
Add to beef mixture.
Cook 5 minutes or until thickened.
Serve on cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soup, milk, rice, and Cheese Whiz to celery and onion.
Mix well until melted.
Thaw broccoli and add to pan.
Add mushrooms if desired.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving liquid.
Layer asparagus in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place French fried onions over asparagus mixture.
Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and juice saved from asparagus.
Pour over French fried onions.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over this and heat in a 350° oven until mixture is just bubbly and cheese melts.
Serve at once.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: apple rolls with custard sauce
directions: Prepare crust for 10-inch two-crust pie.
Roll into rectangular shape on floured board.
Spread apples over dough. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Slice 3/8-inch thick.
Place in baking dish, cut side up.
Melt butter in hot water.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add to liquid and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer, in order, all ingredients except cheese.
Cook, covered with foil, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Grate sharp Cheddar cheese over dish.
Put back in oven for about 5 minutes or until melted completely.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and walnuts.
Add enough salad dressing to moisten.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Crumble sausage into a skillet and cook until brown. Drain well.
Line bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, pressing edges together to seal. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients together well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand about 10 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot cranberry drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in large coffeepot and perk.

title: vidalia sweet onion sausage casserole
directions: Put onions in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Add Ritz crackers and then add sausage.
Add a layer of onions; add cream of mushroom soup.
Top with cheese and pimento.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: "philly" fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange cookie slices, slightly overlapping, on aluminum foil-covered 14-inch pizza pan. Press edges to seal.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool. Remove from foil onto plate.

title: scallop-shrimp kabobs
directions: Place scallops, shrimp, tomatoes and green pepper cubes on skewers; sprinkle with seafood seasoning.
Grill over charcoal or broil in oven until done, basting frequently with butter.
Prepare rice according to package directions; place in serving dish. Place kabobs on rice; serve.

title: nutty blue cheese veggie dip
directions: In a medium, combine mayo, sour cream, blue cheese, onions and bouillon. Mix well. Stir in nuts, cover and chill. Stir before serving. Serve with vegetables.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and oats.
Cut butter into flour mixture until crumbly.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, sugar, flour, soda, salt and egg together, stirring well in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Cover with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake in oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and sugar well.
Add 2 cups cold water and mix again.
Form into balls.
Form into enough balls for 1 crust and wrap.
Dough makes 19 or 20 crusts.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
Then store in plastic bags.

title: carrot apple raisin cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; blend thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except for icing.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini with mozzarella
directions: Cook zucchini for about 20 minutes, or until very tender. Drain in strainer; shake and drain more.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with the Mozzarella cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly in center.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in pan and melt in oven.
Slosh melted butter around pan to grease edges of pan. Place all ingredients (except fruit) in bowl and mix with mixer or hand.
Pour into pan with melted margarine.
Layer fruit over batter; if you saved your juice, pour it over batter.
Bake for 30 minutes or until batter covers fruit and browns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hilda's baked sweet potatoes
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with mixer.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish for 1 hour at 300°.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mash Blue cheese and combine with mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Mash with fork or process in blender if smoother texture is desired.
Serve with celery and carrot sticks.

title: flemish asparagus
directions: Make a stock with cold water. Add the cleaned peels and bottom parts of the asparagus. Add 1 teaspoon sugar, salt, pepper and nutmeg to taste. Boil the asparagus in the strained stock until tender.
Put about 4 asparagus per person on a plate. Garnish with 1 crushed boiled egg.
Pour about 2 tablespoons melted butter over the egg.
Add parsley. Serve with bread or rolls, as an hors d'oeuvre or with boiled potatoes as a meal.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add sour milk and boiling water.
Grease and flour cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cover oiled pan with a layer of corn tortillas.
Layer of chicken.
Mix mushroom soup, broth, olives, chilies and onion; pour 1/2 over chicken.
Add a layer of mixed cheeses.
Start second layer:
tortillas, chicken, etc.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: snack mix
directions: Fry bacon. Drain on paper towel and crumble. Break the pretzel sticks in half. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well.

title: tom's peanut butter snack..."glop"
directions: Put all ingredients in a cereal bowl.
Stir with your teaspoon and then eat!

title: dip with pizza taste
directions: Excellent dip for your favorite raw vegetables or chips.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Cook sausage, crumbling with fork.
Add cheese and mix well. Spread on bread slices and freeze on cookie sheet.
Store in freezer in plastic bag until ready to use.
To cook, place frozen pizzas on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

title: broccoli "n" turkey roll ups
directions: Place frozen broccoli in colander, run hot water over it until thawed.
Drain well.
In large skillet bring to boiling, then reduce to simmer.

Place broccoli on edge of meat portion, roll meat around broccoli, if necessary, secure with toothpick. Carefully place rolls, seam side down, cover skillet and steam about 10 minutes or until it is heated through.
While rolls are steaming, split and toast muffins.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine ingredients and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables for 15 minutes.
Strain, then add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole and place pieces of cheese throughout.
Add paprika to top and bake for 20 minutes. Delicious.

title: frozen custard
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and salt. Pour scalded milk over beaten mixture.
Return to double boiler and cook until coats a spoon.
Allow mixture to cool.
Add cream and vanilla.
Freeze.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: orzo with garlic and parmesan cheese
directions: Boil water and add salt. Add the orzo. Cook and stir about 15 minutes or until tender. Remove 1/4 cup of the liquid and drain the orzo.

Heat oil and butter in saucepan and add garlic. Cook briefly, stirring, but do not brown. Add the drained orzo, orange rind, the reserved cooked liquid, parsley, cheese and black pepper. Toss well. Serve immediately.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, milk and well beaten egg yolks in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Pour in raisins; let cool.
Pour in baked and cooled pie shell.
Top with meringue made from the three egg whites.

title: marshmallow treat
directions: Melt
butter
and marshmallows, then add Rice Krispies. Pour into a pan, about 9 x 11-inch. Cool, slice and serve.

title: quick supper #1
directions: Heat olive oil.
Saute onion, garlic and celery.
Put in meat and brown.
Add seasoning, tomatoes and water; cook 30 minutes (low-medium heat burner).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large saucepan, cook spaghetti; drain and set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan or large skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Lower heat and stir in milk and broth gradually. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving half of Parmesan cheese to put on top.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Boil broccoli until slightly tender.
Place broccoli in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish. Combine soups, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Melt margarine and mix with the bread crumbs.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let cool. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well with a spoon. Pour into a mold or bowl and chill until set.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add the ice cream and spices.
Serve 2 to 3 tablespoons in cup or mug.
Add one jigger of rum and fill with boiling water.
Makes 2 quarts.
Keep in refrigerator until serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Combine bread cubes to celery in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken over cubes, spreading to cover.
Sprinkle with onions.
Combine eggs, soup, milk, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Combine flour and cheese; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over casserole and top with almonds.

title: swiss pepper steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine onion salt, black pepper and flour.
Cut Swiss steak into 6 serving size pieces.
Pound flour mixture into each side of Swiss steak.
Brown in oil.
Arrange in single layer in baking dish.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil pasta 6 to 7 minutes.
Add broccoli to water.
Cook another 2 minutes; drain.
Saute butter, pepper and onion; soften. Stir in flour.
Stir about 1 minute until thick.
Stir in cream, milk and wine.
Keep stirring.
Just before it boils, add Ricotta. Blend in.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/3 cup of Cheddar and Parmesan until melted.
Mix all 3 mixtures together (chicken, broccoli and sauce).

title: billy goat cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and eggs, heat at medium. Temperature for 2 or 3 minutes. Add milk.
Stir in pecans and chopped dates. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in the oven.
When melted, take from oven and spread the graham crackers evenly in the pan.
Then layer the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, sweetened condensed milk, coconut and nuts. Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.
When cool, slice into squares.

title: orange ring
directions: Mix together sugar and orange skin.
Dip each biscuit first in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Stand in ring mold or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt together margarine and 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar. Combine with graham crackers.
Put in oven at 350° for a few minutes (10 minutes) in long baking dish.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup of confectioners sugar.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Put on cracker crumbs.
Put in refrigerator a while.
Add pie filling on top of all.

title: chicken strata
directions: Mix all together and divide between two buttered casseroles. Let stand overnight.
Just before baking, combine 1 can mushroom soup, 2 beaten eggs and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour this over casseroles.
Sprinkle more cheese on top and bake until silver knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy pork chop bake
directions: Brown meat.
Place in glass baking dish.
Mix soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Place onion slice on top of each pork chop. Cover with sauce mixture.

title: hot slaw
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Save the bacon grease.
To the 1/4 cup of grease in the skillet, add sugar, water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over shredded cabbage.
Add crumbled bacon.
Serve hot!

title: hearty onion soup
directions: Cook onions in oil and butter in pot over medium heat, stirring frequently for 30 minutes or until softened and caramelized.
Stir in flour to coat onions.
Cook 1 minute.
Slowly stir in broth. Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Spoon soup into 6 individual ovenproof bowls.
Top each with bread and cheese.
Broil briefly to melt cheese.
Total cooking time:
50 minutes.

title: cheesy rice squares
directions: Mix together the rice, cheese, parsley, onion and salt. Combine eggs, milk and Worcestershire sauce and add it to the rice mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish (or spray with Pam cooking spray, then pour in rice mixture). Bake in a slow 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set. Serves 6 to 9.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and form into a ball. Chill 15 minutes. Roll in nuts. Then serve with your favorite crackers.

title: dilled salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in loaf pan (sprayed with Pam) for 35 to 45 minutes at 325° (or until done and still a little moist).
Leftovers make good sandwiches.

title: catfish mull
directions: Fry fat back, preferably in cast-iron pot with lid.
Remove fat back from pot.
Put a layer of onions, layer of fish, etc. Lay whole peeled potatoes on top.
Add seasoning and oleo.
Put lid on pot; cook until potatoes are done.
Will serve at least 12 people.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl of mixer let eggs warm to room temperature, about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with soda, salt, cloves, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Beat in oil and pumpkin to blend well.
At low speed, beat flour mixture just until combined.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until surface springs back when touched.
Cool cake completely in pan.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken, covered in salted water.
Remove chicken from broth; reserve broth.
Debone chicken; cut into pieces and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients with enough water to form a soft dough (about 4 tablespoons).
Roll dough thinly on a floured board; cut into strips.
Return broth to heat; bring to a boil. Pinch dough off into small pieces; drop into boiling broth.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add chicken to dumplings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and oil. Set aside for 20 minutes. Beat eggs, then add sugar and vanilla and continue beating. Sift dry ingredients. Blend with oats into mixture. Pour batter into two 8-inch greased and floured cake pans or an oblong cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese (reserve 1 cup for topping), eggs, spinach, oregano, salt and pepper in a large bowl. In greased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 noodles and 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat, then top with remaining noodles. Add remaining sauce.
Top with reserved Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edge of pan.
Cover with foil tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until bubbly.
Let stand before serving.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Crush the graham crackers.
Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and nuts. Add to crumbs.
Beat egg whites; add salt and 1/2 cup sugar. Fold into yolk mixture.
Butter a pie plate well.
Pour in batter. Cook at 325° until golden.
Do not overcook.

title: goulash
directions: Cut up round steak as in stew.
Brown beef and sliced onions. Add celery.
Add tomato sauce, peas and carrots (sliced).
Thicken as in gravy and pour over 1 1/2 cups cooked rice.
Simmer stew about 1 hour before thickening.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until cream cheese is partially dissolved.
Add enough water to the pineapple juice to make 1 cup of liquid.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add pineapple.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into jello mixture. Refrigerate.

title: fried quail
directions: Shake birds in bag in mixture of flour, salt, garlic and pepper.
Heat a frying pan half filled with oil.
Brown quail on both sides.
Cover skillet and reduce heat.
Cook slowly until tender, about 30 minutes, turning once or twice to brown evenly. Serves 4.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Put roast in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix. Add ginger ale.
Cover.
Bake at 250° (low heat) about 8 hours. (Can add canned mushrooms toward the end, if you wish.)

title: yankee doodle dandy
directions: On a large sheet of heavy-duty foil or triple thickness of regular foil, sprinkle half package of soup mix.
Place the meat on top and sprinkle remaining soup mix.
Drizzle with tomato juice. Wrap foil tightly and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Open foil and arrange onion and carrots around meat.
Rewrap and bake an additional hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over steaming bed of egg noodles.

title: green bean and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute onion, garlic and olive oil (microwave 3 to 5 minutes). Add green beans (microwave 5 minutes).
Add everything else and heat until hot.
(If you use oven, heat at 350° for 30 minutes.)

title: rolls (jelly)
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; must be sifted.
Now add soft shortening, egg and milk.
Mix until blended.
Grease pans (I prefer paper-liners).
Spoon part of mixture in bottom of muffin pan.
Then add raspberry or blackberry jelly in middle.
Then spoon more of the mixture on top to cover jelly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check muffins before time is up.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Layer one can green beans in buttered casserole dish; salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Mix soup and milk and pour 1/2 mixture over beans.
Add layer of 1/2 the onion rings.
Repeat layers, ending with onion rings.
Top casserole with dots of cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover just before taking from oven and brown lightly.

title: cheese horse puffs
directions: Make these cheese crackers ahead. Refrigerate and heat at 375° until puffed just before serving.

title: myrtle's mexican hot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in pan and heat.
Simmer until done.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler.
Mix in peanuts and Chinese noodles.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and allow to set before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook white rice in chicken broth.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add rice when done.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Brown top under broiler.

title: bread n butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Cover with water and soak for 2 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Add cucumbers, onions and salt mixture and cook until they start to get clear or change color (10 to 15 minutes).
Set jars and lids in hot water and fill jars with pickles.
Seal tightly.

title: chili
directions: Combine first two ingredients in a large saucepan.
Brown and drain off fat.
Add next ingredients and stir until blended. Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with crackers.

title: puffy omelet
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar beating until stiff but not dry.
In small bowl, at medium speed, beat yolks with 1/4 cup cold water and salt until very light and fluffy.
Fold into whites.
In a skillet, heat butter.
Add egg mixture.
Cook over low heat 3 minutes until puffy and golden on bottom when lifted with spatula.
Bake 10 minutes until light brown and center springs when lightly touched. Run spatula around sides to loosen omelet. Make cut through center.
Fold in half and slide out.
Serves 3 to 4.
Top with Shrimp Sauce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream bananas well.
Add oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add melted margarine and sugar.
Then add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add nuts and raisins. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until tester comes out clean. Use loaf pans that been greased and floured.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: sherried beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Saute margarine, onion and pepper until tender.
Add flour. Add cream of chicken soup, milk and chicken broth.
Cook until thick.
Add chicken and top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bar cake(simple and fast)
directions: Mix together the oleo, flour and brown sugar.
Remove 1 cup of mixture for topping; set aside.
To remaining sugar, flour and oleo mixture, add egg, baking soda and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Put the 1 cup of flour-sugar mixture over batter. Crush Heath bars and sprinkle over the top.
(Can use chopped nuts, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend by hand until creamy.
Now add sugar mixing until fluffy.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar
well.
Add egg and molasses. Combine
flour,
salt, soda and spices; add to creamed mixture and mix
well.	Roll
stiff dough into small balls and roll in sugar; place
on
greased cookie sheet.
Indent very slightly with tip of	finger,
but
don't flatten.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sue's special fudge for wayne
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugar.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Boil 5 minutes (rolling boil). Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved.
Add unsweetened chocolate, chocolate chips and sweet chocolate.
Stir until all are melted.
Add nuts; stir well.
(May add 7 ounces flaked coconut if desired.)
Pour onto lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish in oven.
Add water and rice; add onion, celery, broccoli.
Spread undiluted soup over all. Spread Cheez Whiz over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add Mexe-Beans and taco seasoning.
(If too thick, may add a little water.)
Break up lettuce in bowl and add chopped onion and tomatoes. Pour dressing over preceding ingredients.
Put meat mixture next and top with cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: mom's egg custard cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg custard mix, milk and eggs. Blend at low speed until smooth.
Add cake mix and nutmeg.
Blend and beat per package directions.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: surprise turkey
directions: Prepare turkey as usual for baking. Salt and pepper to taste. In cavity, put celery, apple and onions. Put bird on roasting rack and pour 1 quart water in pan. Put tight cover on pan. This is a must! Preheat oven to 475°. Bake 1 hour and turn oven off. Do not open oven until the next morning! Your turkey will be done and your broth ready to go into the dressing.

title: memaw's meatloaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, hot sauce, baking powder, eggs.
Mix in vegetables and hamburger well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Ovens may vary.

title: rayta
directions: Dice cucumber and green pepper.
Add salt.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Drain and squeeze out extra moisture.
Stir yogurt in bowl for 5 minutes.
Add cucumber, coconut, sugar and green pepper.
Stir again.
Rub cumin seed and add.
Stir again.
Put in refrigerator if prepared early.

title: broccoli whiz
directions: Bring water, onion and margarine to boil.
Add broccoli.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rice; let stand 5 minutes. Add cheese and soup.
Mix and put into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash dressing
directions: Add baking powder to cornbread mix and prepare as directed on package.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add squash, onion and bell pepper.
Saute until tender.
Transfer to casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Crumble cornbread and add to mixture, stirring slightly.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Layer ribs in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Brush with lemon juice. Add 1/2 onion. Bake 30 minutes at 450°.

title: snitzel
directions: Stir all ingredients together until a stringy consistency. Boil water.
With a vegetable strainer, strain mixture through into rapidly boiling water.
Use spatula or back of spoon as press.
Boil 6 to 8 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: gravy lovers pot roast
directions: In hot oil and butter in large heavy pot over medium heat, brown roast along with sliced onion, turning until browned on all sides.
Add thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Add beef broth, water and all other ingredients except carrots.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 2 hours, turning so it will cook evenly.
Add carrots and cook 1 more hour.
Remove meat and carrots and strain liquid into a bowl.
Return strained liquid to the pot.
In 1/3 cup water, mix 2 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch. Pour in pot and bring to a boil.
Put carrots back and serve carrots with the gravy.

title: bombocado-brazilian egg custard
directions: Beat sugar and eggs in the blender.
Add remaining ingredients and beat again.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Insert knife in center to test for doneness.

title: kahlua or liquor cake
directions: Beat egg whites with granulated sugar until stiff peaks form. Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Beat in yolks one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with coffee and Kahlua.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and water.
When thick, add Cheez Whiz.
Combine sauce with broccoli and eggs. Pour in greased casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 360°.

title: taco salad
directions: In frying pan fry hamburger.
Add kidney beans, onion, garlic, chilies, salt and pepper.
In large bowl tear up about 1/2 the head of lettuce.
Dice tomatoes.
Cut the olives in half.
Add Cheddar cheese, as much as you like.
In a small bowl mix sour cream and hot sauce to taste.
In the large bowl with lettuce add 1/2 bag Doritos and meat mix on top.
Add about 1/2 sour cream and mix all together.
Looks gross, tastes great.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt butter in pie pan.
Add flour and powdered sugar. Mix until blended.
Pat flat with handle and flute edges.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift together flours, salt and soda.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and beat in egg until smooth and creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients, then add pumpkin and orange rind.
Fold in buttermilk, nuts and spices. Bake for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans or into 1 Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done (top will split).
Cool for 5 to 8 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle cake with confectioners sugar.

title: cabbage bean soup(low-fat)
directions: In a large saucepan, sprayed with butter flavored cooking spray (or Pam), saute onion until tender.
Add water, ham, cabbage, tomatoes, chili seasoning mix and pepper.
Bring to a boil; lower heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans; simmer 20 more minutes.
Servings:
4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.
Calories: 169; 2 gm fat.

title: no pastry coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients as given, except coconut. Then add coconut. Pour into large pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain pineapple.
Arrange fruit on mixture in pan. Mix cake mix into batter following directions on box.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Invert on plate.
Let syrup drain onto cake before removing pan.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in large Tupperware pan.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: white chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter and shortening in a mixing bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer; add melted chocolate.
Gradually add 1/2 of the powdered sugar; beat well.
Add salt, flavorings and lemon juice.
Gradually add remaining powdered sugar and whipping cream alternately, beginning and ending with sugar.
Mix well after each addition.

title: vegetable supreme pizza
directions: Spread out the pizza dough in a 10 x 12-inch baking pan. Spread the can of pizza sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of sauce.
Cut up your vegetables and put them on top of your cheese.
Heat the oven to 350° and bake.
After taking out of the oven, just serve and enjoy.

title: coconut brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients (butter, flour and 4 tablespoons brown sugar).
Bake in a 9-inch square pan in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Mix other ingredients, adding each in the order listed. Spread this on top of first mixture; bake again for a half hour. Makes 2 dozen.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and make into small balls.
Roll in crushed cracker crumbs.
Brown in 3 tablespoons shortening.
Place in baking dish.
Put 1 can mushroom soup and 3/4 cup water (mixed together) over meatballs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: golden autumn salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine golden raisins and honey Dijon salad dressing.
Let raisin mixture stand 1 hour.
Thinly slice 1 pear and cut second pear into 1/4-inch cubes.
In separate large bowl, combine honey Dijon-raisin mixture, pear slices and cubes, walnuts and fresh spinach.
Toss salad to coat evenly. Serve chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tomato butter
directions: Peel and slice tomatoes.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Mix cinnamon, ginger root and cloves; place in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to tomato mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Makes 4 pints.

title: plum slush
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Makes 4 servings, 84 calories per serving.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles.
Cut into chunks.
Place dill chunks back in gallon jar, layering pickles with sugar, garlic and Tabasco sauce.
Let sit for one week, rotating jar from top to bottom each day.
Chill and enjoy.

title: texas fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pack into individual loaf or Bundt pans.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before removing from pans.

title: witches brew chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in a large dutch-oven over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and next three ingredients and saute 10 minutes.
Stir in broth and next three ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes.
Stir in 2 cans of beans and chilies.
Mash remaining can of beans in a small bowl. Whisk together flour and milk and stir into beans.
Gradually add bean mixture to soup mixture; stirring constantly.
Cook 10 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in cilantro.
Serve with desired toppings.
Make a salad, grab some crusty bread and you've got a complete meal.

title: butterscotch pear ice cream soda
directions: Reserve 1 slice pear for garnish.
Puree remaining pear. Combine pear puree and butterscotch sauce; mix well.
Place in bottom of a glass.
Add ice cream.
Fill with club soda.
Garnish side of glass with pear slice.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder into bowl. Mix in beaten egg, orange juice and melted butter.
Add hot water, pecans and cranberry halves.
Use loaf pan 8 x 4 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 to 6 minutes and turn onto wire rack to cool 8 to 10 minutes.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: holiday potatoes(scrumptious)
directions: Mix together ingredients. Pour in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until bubbly. May sprinkle on more cheese and paprika; bake another 10 minutes for a crispy top.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Melt margarine in a 14-inch Dutch oven.
Brown meat and season to
taste.
Cut
vegetables into bite-sized pieces and add to meat.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 can cream of mushroom soup, rice, corn and mushrooms.
Add the other 2 cans of soup
and enough water to fill Dutch oven.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours with
12 coals
on
top
and
coals
on the bottom. Replenish coals if necessary.

title: reuben dip(spread)
directions: Shred cheese and cut beef into small pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with party size rye or pumpernickel bread.
Spread on as desired.

title: hot cheese rolls
directions: Mix cheeses and pecans in mixing bowl (with hands) until thoroughly blended.
Add Tabasco sauce and mix well.
Divide in half.
Roll in hands to form long roll.
Place on wax paper which is covered with paprika.
Roll cheese until covered.
Wrap in same paper and refrigerate.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with foil.
Combine first four ingredients.
Melt butter; add garlic, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Dip breasts in butter, then in breadcrumb mixture, coating heavily.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello with strawberries (frozen berries may be used, thawed).
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place marshmallows in pan.

title: butterfly gelatin salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until completely dissolved.
Add cold water, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 cup of the mixture into 9-inch round cake pan.
Set aside.

title: yam patties
directions: Place in container.
Blend until smooth.
Shape into patties and dip into 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Fry in butter until light brown.
Serves 4.

title: banana dream dessert(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Crust:
Mix together crushed crackers, melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: spring fling
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges with mixer until well blended.
There will be small chunks of oranges.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans for 35 minutes or until done. Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove when cold and split layers to make 4 layers.

title: relish
directions: Combine the chopped green tomatoes and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Grind the peppers and cabbage.
Combine all ingredients and cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: amanda liston's salad
directions: Toss in bowl lettuce, eggs and onion.
Whisk together Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar until smooth.
Combine.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Prepare instant pudding, chill to set.
When cool, cut cake into squares.
Put a layer in bottom of trifle bowl; top with layer of pudding and Heath bars (crack on counter).
Then put layer of Cool Whip; continue with layers ending with Cool Whip.
Dive in and enjoy.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Press out crescent rolls into 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet. Bake until lightly browned.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over cooked crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables.
Top with cheese and press down.
Serve at room temperature.
(Make day before serving.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges in blender or processor. Add sugar and stir.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and mix with fruit.
Add chopped nuts if desired.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet 'n' sour sausage
directions: Parboil sausage approximately 15 to 20 minutes to remove excess fat.
Fry sausage thoroughly until brown on all sides. Drain and cut into bite-size pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients in frying pan.
Simmer 5 minutes and add sausage.
Heat sausage until sauce bubbles.
Serve hot with toothpicks.
Keeps well in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: old fashion fudge cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add and mix for one minute next four ingredients.
Last, add and mix hot water.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 pan or 12 x 18 cookie sheet pan at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate butter cream icing.

title: herbed pecans
directions: In heavy skillet, melt margarine; stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt, cinnamon, garlic, cayenne and hot pepper sauce.
Add pecans.
Toss until nuts are well coated.
Place in single layer in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring often until nuts are brown and crisp. Makes about 4 cups.

title: cousin doris overton's poor man's cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease and flour 9 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: After mixing shortening, flour and salt, add ice water to make a ball. Poke holes in the bottom and sides after rolling the dough and place in a pie dish.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Add to other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken breasts royale
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chipped beef in bottom of pan. Place chicken breasts on top of beef.
Place slightly fried bacon on top of chicken breasts.
Blend soup and sour cream.
Spoon over meat, covering all pieces completely with mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.
Serve warm, using gravy as topping for rice or mashed potatoes.

title: aunt yvonne's popsicles
directions: Mix together until sugar and jello dissolve.
Put in Dixie cups.
Don't forget to put in the sticks.

title: frances' bean supreme
directions: Partially drain and mix all beans in large ovenproof pan. Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Drain excess fat and mix meat with beans.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Can also be done in large crock-pot.
You may also substitute your favorite beans for any on list; just keep amounts the same.

title: cranberry sparkle
directions: Place ice mold or cubes in punch bowl; add juices.
Stir. Pour carbonated beverage carefully down side of bowl.
Float scalloped orange slices if desired.
Simple as 1-2-3.
Plenty of pep!

title: lima beans with chestnuts and fresh rosemary
directions: In a large skillet, melt the butter.
Add chestnuts and saute 5 minutes.
Add the lima beans and rosemary and continue to saute another 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings. Preparation time:
5 minutes; cooking time:
10 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in picante sauce and water until done.
Debone and break into pieces.
Mix 1/2 can water and chicken soup together.
Alternate tortillas, chicken, chicken soup and cheese. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chili dip
directions: Heat chili and cream cheese in saucepan over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring frequently.
Serve with corn chips or nachos.
Yield:
32 servings.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: almond baked fish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in	a
x
2-inch baking dish. Arrange fish in
dish.
Spread
mayonnaise	over
fish. Combine cracker crumbs, 3
tablespoons butter or margarine and almonds. Sprinkle over fish.
Bake at
400°	for
or
15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Roll pretzels with rolling pin until fine.
Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; let cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in seasoned water with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Debone chicken.
Melt margarine in a pan and saute onion and bell pepper.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat on low.
Cook pasta in chicken broth.
Drain.
Add chicken and pasta to sauce.
Put in dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.
You can add 1 cup celery to saute.
You can also add 1 can mushrooms, black olives, chopped tomatoes or substitute cream of chicken soup in place of cream of mushroom soup.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to make 1 cup, bring to boil. Stir in jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce. Chill until thick.
Add pineapple.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Place unthawed hash browns in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Heat soup, butter, cheese and sour cream on medium heat until cheese is melted.
Spoon over potatoes.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: crabbies-appetizer
directions: Blend softened butter, cheese, mayonnaise, crab meat and garlic powder.
Spread on muffin halves and cut into quarters.
To serve immediately, bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Can be frozen and baked or broiled later.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in only 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9x13 dish and refrigerate until set.
Remove and spread sour cream evenly over it.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Pour on top the rest of the Jello mixture.	Refrigerate until firm.
Great with Cool Whip on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In casserole dish, place 1/2 stuffing mix (follow box directions). Save half of seasoning pack.
Then add 1/2 soup mixture, chicken pieces, remainder of soup and remainder of stuffing mix.
