Mix 1 stick butter, remainder of seasoning pack from dressing and broth; bring to a boil.
Pour over casserole. Cover and cook until bubbling (about 30 minutes), at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Brown hamburger and

onion. Combine hamburger, spaghetti and pizza sauces and sugar. Combine cheeses. In crock-pot, place a layer of pasta, followed by a layer of hamburger mix, then mushrooms, then cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Last layer should be cheese. Warm in crock-pot until cheese melts.

title: jalapeno and cheddar bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in part of the water. Add cornmeal, honey and salt in a large bowl and gradually add flour until dough forms and pulls away from the sides of the bowl. Add the peppers and cheese and mix.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured bowl and knead until you have a good dough. Place in a greased mixing bowl and cover with a damp cloth.

Let rise until doubled in bulk. Punch dough down and let rise for another hour. Punch down and divide into 2 equal parts. Form into loaves and place in loaf pans. Let rise until doubled in bulk and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms well; trim stems.
Put all ingredients into a large heavy-duty Ziploc bag or tight sealing container.
Seal and shake gently to coat mushrooms and olives.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour prior to serving.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes. Place in saucepan and add enough water to completely cover by 1/2-inch. Bring to slow boil and cook approximately 45 minutes. Add butter, seasonings and wine. If soup appears too thin, add a can of potato soup or a small amount of instant mashed potatoes until mixture reaches desired consistency. When all is blended together, add cheese, which has been cut into small pieces. Mix until cheese has completely melted and serve hot.

title: crabmeat on english muffins
directions: Mix together.
Spread on split English muffin.
Partially freeze for 15 minutes.
Then cut in quarters and freeze until ready to use.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Press dough evenly into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 -15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Place cookie crust on serving plate.
Spread cool whip on cookie crust and garnish with fruit.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: r.j.'s chile
directions: Place chile brick in pan over low heat and stir.
Cook ground beef in skillet and brown.
Pour off grease from beef.
Add ground beef to chile brick.
Stir frequently.
Add tomato paste (water as needed), green pepper, onion, chile powder, chile seasoning, salt, black pepper and catsup to taste.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes; stir frequently.

title: company chicken breasts
directions: Place layer of dried beef in bottom of greased baking dish. Arrange bacon wrapped chicken breasts on beef slices.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover pan tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
When tender, remove foil and let brown slightly.
May be prepared the day before and refrigerated.

title: hopkins county (texas) stew
directions: Cook tomatoes and onion in a large stew pot. Add 2 cans water. Cut potatoes into bite-size and cook separately until tender. Add potatoes to tomato mixture. Add salt, pepper and chili powder. Add chicken along with part of chicken stock. Let cook for awhile. Add corn last, stirring often so corn will not stick. Can add a little sugar and margarine, if desired.

title: grandma's coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease three 9-inch layer cake pans.
Line bottom with waxed paper.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. In large bowl, beat sugar and butter with electric mixer or wooden spoon until pale and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in flour mixture 1/3 at a time, alternating with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
In clean bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form when beaters are lifted.
Fold into batter. Spread evenly in prepared pans.
Bake in middle of oven 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned and pick inserted in centers comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack 10 minutes.
Invert onto rack; remove pans.
Peel off paper and cool layers completely.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in balls. Roll balls in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions.
Drain well; place in large saucepan and set aside. Meanwhile, cook onion in the butter until tender but not brown. Stir in the flour, salt, garlic powder, basil and pepper. Add milk.
Cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Add cream cheese. Stir till cheese melts.
Stir into vegetable mixture. Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Toss together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, and the 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or till heated through. Makes 12 servings.

title: marble-ous peanut butter dessert
directions: In bowl, cream sugar, peanut butter and margarine.
Add flour and blend until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or golden brown.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons margarine until golden brown. Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour remaining 1/4 cup margarine into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss cooked spaghetti in margarine. Cover spaghetti with 1 can tomato sauce.
Add in order listed: one half of the Swiss cheese, one half of the pepperoni, one half of the Mozzarella cheese, all of the onions, then sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Top with remainder of tomato sauce, Swiss cheese, pepperoni and finally the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Place beans in a pan or kettle.
Cover with water and 2 tablespoons of salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain.
Add 2 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 2 hours. In a skillet, saute onion and clove of garlic with beef sausage. Add 1 small can stewed tomatoes and flavoring content.
Simmer for 5 minutes, then add to bean pot.
Simmer an additional hour.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs and add salt, vanilla and milk.
Pour into a casserole and place casserole in hot water and bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Run blade of silver knife in custard and if knife comes out clean, remove from oven and water.
Chill. Sprinkle nutmeg on top as desired before serving.

title: texas biscuits
directions: Mix all together.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Fill 1/2.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: vegetarian eggrolls in tomato sauce
directions: Combine cream cheese, eggs, stuffing, finely chopped onion, nuts and salt.
In a skillet, saute large onion and celery.
Add tomatoes; set aside.
Form cream cheese mixture into patties by dropping them from a tablespoon into oil in skillet.
Brown both sides, shaping them into patties.
After browning, place them in a casserole dish.
Pour tomato mixture over patties and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool and remove from bone, saving broth. Partially cook broccoli.
Layer chicken, broccoli, salt, cheese and stuffing (dry) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine broth and soups. Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Roll out pastry a little less than 1/8-inch thick and cut into 7-inch squares.
Pare and core apples for each dumpling.
Boil next 4 ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Place apple on each square of pastry.
Fill cavities of apples with mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Dot each with butter. Bring opposite points of pastry up over the apple.
Overlap, moisten and seal.
Lift carefully, place a little apart in baking dish.
Pour hot syrup around dumplings.
Bake immediately 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is nicely browned and apples are cooked through.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Slice orange and lemon into flat slices.
Pour together lime, cranberry and grenadine juice.
Add rum if wanted.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Saute minced garlic in olive oil.
Pour stewed tomatoes into oil and simmer.
Add your spices at this time.
Cover; simmer about 40 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Add crumbled Feta cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground meat; drain well.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add meat.
Stir into large serving bowl.
You may want to garnish with sour cream.
Great for summer!

title: peach or fig fruit preserves
directions: To keep celery crisp, stand it in a jar of cold salted water and refrigerate.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Take a cup of Consideration and a cup of Courtesy, then 2 cupfuls of Flattery (carefully concealed).
Add 2 cupfuls of Milk of Human Kindness.
Blend 1 gallon of Faith in God and each other with 2 cupfuls of Praise.
Mix a small pinch of In-Laws and a Reasonable Budget with a generous dash of Cooperation.
Add extract of "I'm sorry."
Add the Confidence and Encouragement. Have at least 2 Children and 1 large or several small Hobbies.
Add 1 cup Blindness to each other's faults.
Flavor with frequent portions of Recreation and a Dash of Happy Memories; stir well. Remove any specks of Jealousy, Temper or Criticism.
Sweeten with generous portions of Love; keep warm with a steady Flame of Devotion.
Never serve with a cold shoulder or hot tongue!

title: chicken rolls
directions: Place each piece of chicken between two pieces of waxed paper; pound thin, at least 1/4-inch thick.
On each piece of chicken, place 1/2 slice of cheese and 1/2 slice ham.
May add a small sprig of sage or dill at this time.
Roll each piece and secure with a toothpick.
Dip each piece in flour, then in beaten egg, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until lightly browned on both sides, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: apple roasted duck
directions: Clean and wash ducks thoroughly.
Mix apples, raisins and bread crumbs.
Pour in 1/2 to 3/4 cup apple juice and mix until moist. Fill ducks with mixture.
Rub ducks with onion slice, salt and pepper.
Baste with remaining apple juice.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake in oven at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves six.

title: island dessert
directions: Pour pineapple in bowl with juice, add marshmallows to bowl. Stir well.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Put in refrigerator for at least 3 hours, or overnight.
Spoon into serving dishes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix
all ingredients in a crock or glass container. Do NOT use metal.	Leave overnight at room temperature.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Beat eggs, oleo and sugar until smooth.
Fold bread and pineapple into egg mixture.
Pour into greased 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stir and roll pizza
directions: Stir all ingredients until mixture leaves side of bowl.
Press into ball; knead 10 times in bowl until smooth.
Divide in half. Roll in 13-inch circle.
Put in pan; turn up edges and pinch. Put on toppings and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.,

title: yankee pot roast
directions: The large end of a chuck roast is easily cut into slices for steaks, casseroles or roulades.
Brown meat on all sides in heavy skillet.
Add soup.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is done, about 3 to 4 hours.
Remove meat.
Thicken gravy with smooth paste made by blending 1/4 cup water with 2 to 4 tablespoons flour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and dates.
Cook 6 to 10 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Cool. Roll in balls in coconut.

title: squash casserole
directions: Have squash hot.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Add soup; do not dilute.
Add onion flakes and 1/2 cup herbed crumbs (I use Pepperidge Farm).
Add cheese.
Top with rest of crumbs.
Bake at 325° until bubbly.

title: eastern shore clam cakes(yields 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Drain juice from clams (save for later in recipe).
Mince clams fine.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Chop up dried beef very fine.
Blend cream cheese and milk. Mix other ingredients with this, except for the nuts.
Put into 8-inch pie plate.
Spread chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a baked pie shell (or a graham cracker crust pie shell).
Freeze for 6 hours before serving.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix well and bake on cookie sheet.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into round ball and serve on a round plate.
Eat on crackers.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Finely crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with margarine.
Press into pie pan and bake at 350° for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Let cool. Combine evaporated milk, marshmallows and chocolate chips in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until chocolate chips are completely melted and mixture is thick.
Cool. Place 1/2 of ice cream in shell.
Cover with 1/2 of chocolate mixture.
Add remaining 1/2 of ice cream and top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Decorate with pecans, if desired.

title: easy chocolate delight
directions: Bake any chocolate cake in a jelly roll pan.
(I used the basic Texas sheet cake.)
Frost while warm.
When cake is cool, cut into small cubes.
Using a glass punch bowl or chip and dip type bowl, layer the cake with Cool Whip, starting with Cool Whip and ending with Cool Whip.
Shave chocolate pieces or other type of decoration on top.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix well; pour over the vegetables.
Let stand overnight.

title: frosted raisin nut bars
directions: Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Sift together salt, cinnamon and flour.
Combine dry ingredients with raisins and nuts.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Spread evenly in well-greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and drizzle with frosting.
Cut in bars.

title: cranberry, pecan muffins
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar and set aside.
In a large bowl, sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add cranberries and sugar. Cut in the shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in the pecans and lemon rind.

Beat eggs with milk and add to flour. Stir until moist and add cranberries, folding in until mixed. Place waxed muffin paper in muffin pan and spoon mixture into pan, filling cups 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° just until bubbly hot. Grate cheese on top and mix in to melt.

title: potato stuffing
directions: Cook potatoes with 1/2 tablespoon salt in boiling water. Drain and mash.
Saute onion and celery in butter 5 minutes.
Add the mashed potatoes, crumbs, salt, sage and thyme.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Beat in egg.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling in ungreased 9 x 13 inch glass pan. Dump crushed pineapple with juice on top of cherries. Spread cake mix [dry] on top of fruit. Slice margarine; lay slices in rows on top of cake mix. Bake at 350 until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Drain Gardinaria, olives, mushrooms and tuna.
Place in a large Tupperware type bowl with a lid.
Add artichokes, tomato sauce and vinegar.
Marinate, turning occasionally, overnight. May be served in lettuce cups or on a buffet.

title: swiss baked eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Crumble 1 slice of bacon for each serving in custard cups.
Add cream and 1 tablespoon Swiss cheese. Add 1 unbeaten egg to each dish and sprinkle with salt.
Set dish in a shallow baking pan filled with water and bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon chives and remaining 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until egg is set.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken-cheese ball
directions: Blend all but pecans in mixing bowl.
Shape into one large ball. Coat with toasted pecans.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook on medium heat until thick, about 1 hour.

title: lemon zucchini bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.
Yields one large loaf.

title: spicy dunk sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Keep in covered jar in refrigerator 2 or 3 days before using.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Melt margarine, add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and milk; beat well.
Add cracker crumbs, baking powder, nuts and coconut; mix well.
Bake 3 layers for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large bowl, combine filling ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool pie before cutting.
Garnish with whipped topping and nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and place in greased dish. Make sauce of butter, flour, salt, milk, pepper and cheese. Sprinkle almonds on broccoli, then pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly, hot and browned on top.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1/2 cup white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk, vanilla, flour, soda and salt. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place a chocolate Kiss in the center of each cookie. Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: chicken and green chile egg rolls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Add water to cover; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until chicken is done.
Pour mixture through a wire mesh strainer into a bowl, discarding broth. Debone chicken and shred meat with a fork.
Combine chicken, cheese and chiles in a large bowl; stir well.
Mound about 1/3 cup filling in center of each egg roll wrapper.
Fold top corner of wrapper over filling, then fold left and right corners over filling.
Lightly brush exposed corner with water.
Tightly roll filled end of wrapper toward exposed corner; gently press cover to seal.

title: potato casserole with instant potatoes
directions: Prepare instant potatoes according to packaged directions for 8; add one beaten egg and mix well.
Add cream cheese, softened, and mix well with electric mixer.
Add onion.
Pour mixture into casserole; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serves 8.

title: quick pizza muffins(pizzette rapide)
directions: This is my husband's favorite.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute
onion in butter; add squash, sour cream, soup, carrot, salt and pepper.
Lay in buttered casserole dish mixture, crumbs, mixture and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine together and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 glass pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 6 - 8 minutes. Allow to cool.
Blend the cream cheese and sugar together and then blend in the Cool Whip.
Spread the cheese mixture over the cooled pretzel crust, making sure to seal the mixture against the sides of the pan.
Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add the strawberries.
Put the jello mixture in the refrigerator to partially set.
When it is partially set, pour it over the cream cheese layer.
Chill until fully set.

title: pepper relish or sandwich spread
directions: Grind
peppers	and
onions;
sprinkle	with salt.
Let stand for several hours or overnight.
Drain good.
Mix flour, sugar and vinegar together.
Heat for a few minutes, stirring constantly to dissolve sugar.	Add pepper mixture and boil for 1
minute. Lower
heat and cook until done.
Stir often as it sticks
easy to	bottom	of pan.
Add mayonnaise and mustard. Get good and hot; turn heat off.
Fill jars and seal.

title: peach blossom fizz
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth and serve.

title: szchuan stir-fry chicken
directions: Combine seasoning with 1/4 cup water and soy sauce.
Set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet (high heat).
Add meat; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and bamboo shoots. Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add seasoning; stir and cook 1 minute. Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour and add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Beat well, until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8 to 9-inch) cake layer pans, lined with paper.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost layer tops only with Coconut-Pecan Icing.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Place in bottom of casserole pan. Brown beef and onion. Add tomato paste and water.
Spread mixture over noodles.
Mix last 3 ingredients and spread over beef mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° enough to heat through (Cheddar cheese for top).

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Let set for 1 hour. Add chicken, beef or other meat and let marinate overnight.
This recipe is for 2 chickens.
Use 1/2 recipe for 1 chicken.
After chicken is marinated, bake in 350° oven until tender, approximately 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 3 1/2 cups milk. Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread half the pudding mix over crackers. Repeat layers, ending with graham crackers.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip first 2 ingredients together in a blender.
Add orange juice; blend until smooth.
Serve with bite-size pieces of fresh fruit (bananas and apple slices are great) to dip and enjoy!

title: coke cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Bring 2 sticks Parkay, 1 cup Coke and 3 tablespoons cocoa to a boil.
Pour over flour-sugar mixture. Combine eggs, buttermilk and soda; beat thoroughly.
Add marshmallows.
Bake 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Bake in a sheet pan, so it will be thin.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Work well.
Add eggs and bread, moistened with milk or water. Add onion (finely chopped or grated) and allspice.
Work with hands until well blended.
Make into small sized balls.
Fry until brown.
Add 1 cup of water.
Simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hours.

title: musliex
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and microwave on High until bubbling (approximately 2 minutes).
Combine remaining ingredients except dried fruit in a large shallow bowl.
Stir in hot mixture. Add fruit.
Microwave on High, stirring often, until mixture turns golden and starts to firm up (approximately 6 to 10 minutes).

title: fireside spice punch
directions: Put pineapple juice, water and cranberry juice in a 8-cup percolator.
Put other ingredients in top basket and perk 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° until it tests done.
Serve with whipped cream or topping if desired.

title: mama's poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole dish.
Stir-fry chicken until done.
Salt and pepper.
Layer ingredients in order.

title: healthy vegi-dill dip
directions: Blend the buttermilk, cottage cheese and yogurt in blender until smooth.
Stir in dill weed to taste.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: eggplant soup with tiny white beans
directions: Warm a large soup pot over medium heat, then add the olive oil.
When it is warm, add the onion, garlic and celery leaves; saute until fragrant and just wilted, about 3 minutes.
Add the eggplant and tomatoes, cover and let the vegetables simmer for about 7 minutes.
Stir in the stock, thyme and rosemary; continue to simmer until the eggplant is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add the beans; heat through.
Serve hot, sprinkled with the Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Follow directions on cookie mix box.
Use greased pizza pan. Spread cookie mixture to cover pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes. After cookie has cooled, mix 10x sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread over cookie.
Garnish with your favorite fruit (strawberries, bananas, kiwi, pineapple, etc.).

title: bourbon wieners
directions: Cut wieners into small bite size pieces.
Mix all other ingredients together; stir in wieners.
Simmer for 1 hour. (Cocktail wieners may be used.
A crock-pot is perfect for simmering.)

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Skin and debone chicken and cut into chunks.
Combine first 5 ingredients; add water and egg and stir until smooth.
Pour the oil in medium saucepan.
Heat until hot; dip chicken into batter, then in breadcrumbs.
Fry until golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: crab meat roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from the bread.
Flatten bread with a rolling pin. Melt Velveeta and 1/2 pound of butter over low heat.
Cool; stir in crab.
Spread on bread slices.
Roll up.
Brush rolls with remaining butter, melted.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place seam side down on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
May be frozen at this point.
When ready to bake, cut in half.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: green beans(canned)
directions: Put green beans in an iron skillet.
Add sugar and oil.
Boil for 30 minutes, or until liquid has evaporated.

title: lemon pineapple gelatin fluff
directions: Mix jello and boiling water well.
Add partially drained pineapple, marshmallows, mayonnaise and cottage cheese immediately.
Mix thoroughly.
Add cherries and nuts before chilling, if desired.
Garnish with cherries when chilled.
Serve with crisp iceberg lettuce.
Uses a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar with whip.
Add onion mixing well.
Add oil a little at a time beating with a mixer.
Add poppy seed.
Mixture will be thick.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Get 1 quart of fresh snow.
Put in large bowl.
Add milk and sugar.
Stir and mix good.
Add vanilla or other flavoring. Freeze for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat at medium speed, scraping often until mixture is light and fluffy (1 to 2 minutes).
Add pumpkin and bananas. Continue beating until well mixed, 1 to 2 minutes.
(Mixture will have curdled appearance.)
Add remaining ingredients except nuts. Mix just until moistened (about 1 minute).
Stir in nuts.
Spread into 2 greased
8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright in pans for 5 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar, cocoa and salt. Cook until smooth. Add vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts. Pour into 9 x 5 pan. Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all together and put in greased muffin pans.
Makes about 12.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough brown sugar until the marinade tastes a little too sweet (very important).
Do not eat ginger root!
A little dry drinking sherry may be added for extra flavor. May be used for beef or chicken.
Best if marinated for at least 8 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine first two ingredients.
Cut biscuits in quarters. Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Layer in buttered Bundt pan or baking dish.
Pour any remaining sugar into 1 cup measure.
Add the additional teaspoon of cinnamon and fill to the top with sugar.
Combine melted butter with one cup of sugar-cinnamon mixture and pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Pull off "one bite" at a time.

title: beef cheese roll
directions: Mix together; shape into 2 rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika. Chill.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Sift flour and measure; sift with sugar, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts, dates, cranberries and orange rind. Combine beaten eggs with buttermilk and oil; add to fruit mixture. Bake in a well-greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix sauce, sugar and eggs.
Add remainder of ingredients. Pour into 8 x 8 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: filipino shower salad
directions: Wash carefully, drain the spinach, tear if needed, into a large salad bowl.
Add a small amount of lettuce, endive or other salad green, just enough to enhance the appearance of the salad.
Add onions, pineapple chunks and be sure to save the liquid from the pineapple.
Add the cooked shellfish and toss well.
This salad refrigerates well in Tupperware if you are preparing it ahead of time.

To make the dressing you combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and the liquid from the pineapple chunks together in the blender. I even add a few pieces of the pineapple to the salad dressing. The cashew nuts are to sprinkle on the top of the salad after the dressing has been added.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Heat all ingredients in microwave (except for nuts) for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Take out and stir, then add nuts.
Stir well, then spread in a buttered, shallow dish.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Mix in order given. Roll into cookie about the size of a finger. Bake at 350° until light brown. Let cool and roll in sugar.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix hamburger, onion, soup, green beans and Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: holiday broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to package directions.
Drain.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs or crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° until browned and bubbly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Stir the cream cheese in bowl until soft.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and the instant pudding and beat very slow, about 1 minute.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
You can cover with your favorite fruit.
Chill in icebox for 2 to 3 hours, covered with plastic wrap.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cream butter; blend in confectioners sugar and 2 cups flour. Press firmly into 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Beat eggs, granulated sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well and pour over hot crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Set the
onions
and
cabbage aside in a separate bowl. Toast the crushed noodles in a dry Teflon skillet until brown. Then add the sesame seed and almonds.
Cool.
Add oriental mix flavoring (comes
in
package
with
noodles).
Prepare
the dressing by combining the soy sauce, vinegar, pepper, oil and sugar.
Mix together just before serving, then add dry ingredients.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Pour margarine on top and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine 1 stick margarine, 1/4 cup cocoa, 1 cup water and oil in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Mix flour, sugar and soda together in large bowl.
Pour cocoa mixture over dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1/2 cup milk and eggs, mixing well.
Pour into large greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Combine remaining 1 stick margarine, 1/4 cup cocoa and 1/3 cup milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add confectioners sugar, salt, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Frost cake and cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas; set aside.
Mix sugar and oil.
Take dry ingredients and alternate with bananas.
Mix well.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Test with toothpick method until done.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel and dice eggplant and cook in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cook onions and mushrooms in butter.
Blend in 4 tablespoons flour and cook for 1 minute.
Stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Add eggplant, slightly drained.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange buttermilk molded salad
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil pineapple and syrup.
Remove from heat, stir in gelatin.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour in 8-cup mold or Pyrex dish.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: shrimp with squash casserole
directions: Moistened in 2 tablespoons butter, drain and rinse shrimp. Melt butter, blend in flour, gradually add milk and cook to smooth sauce; season with salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and squash; layer in buttered casserole alternately with shrimp, sauce and crumbs. Reserve some crumbs for top.
Remove cover and bake 25 minutes in 325° oven.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, margarine and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Spread in pizza pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
(Can use sugar cookie mix.) Cool crust.

title: reese's cup cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients. Stir in flour. Roll into 1-inch balls and drop into mini muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and press one candy into each hot cookie. Makes 2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips last.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Pour butter or margarine into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in brown sugar and ground cloves; spread over bottom of pan.
Arrange peach slices in pattern over sugar mixture.
Prepare yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Spread over sugar and peaches, evenly.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until center springs back when pressed with finger tips.
Loosen edges of cake with knife and immediately invert onto serving plate.
Let stand 1 or 2 minutes.
Lift off pan.
Serve warm or cool.
Makes one 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
The longer it's cooked, the better it is.

title: mom's chicken marinade
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate 1 hour before grilling.

title: twelve bean soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until tender and serve with cornbread.

title: mamie eisenhower's million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk for 6 minutes. Put chocolates and marshmallow cream in a large bowl.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted.
Pour in a pan.

title: 7 layer lettuce salad
directions: Place ingredients in pan in order given, except mayonnaise, sugar and cheese.
Mix the mayonnaise and sugar; spread over salad.
Sprinkle cheese over dressing.
Cover; refrigerate.
Can be made several hours ahead of time.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients well and let set overnight or several hours.
Hollow out onion/rye bread (round).
Fill with mixture just before serving.
Slice bread you removed from center for dipping.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix and pat into a 9
x 12-inch Pyrex dish (greased and floured).

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough out on cookie sheet tray 1/8-inch thick edge to edge.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; spread on cookie crust.
Top with fruit and chill.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Store in refrigerator.
This sauce is particularly good on cream cheese, and cocktail weiners.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar.
Add oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Divide batter in 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove bread from pans and place on cooling rack to finish cooling. Makes 3 loaves.

title: pasta italiano bake
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste, water and seasonings. Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine noodles and parsley.
Toss lightly.

title: creamy delight salad
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze.
(I freeze in muffin pans, using paper liners.)

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 teaspoons cocoa and 3/4 cup sugar.
Stir in milk and melted oleo.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cocoa and spread on top of mixture in baking dish.
Pour water over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
It is very good hot with butter on it.

title: moyashi sesame oil(bean sprout)
directions: Bring water to boil briskly.
Add moyashi; mix and turn off fire.
Leave
just	long
enough to remove raw taste, but crispy. Drain
and	mix
moyashi, green onion and sesame oil. Add salt and aji to taste.

title: best scones
directions: Warm buttermilk; add yeast and dissolve, then add remaining ingredients, flour last.
Dough should be soft.
Let raise double in bulk.
Punch down.
Place in fridge until ready to use.
Pat or roll to 1/3-inch thick.
Slice with knife and fry in hot fat at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanuts in saucepan and heat, stirring constantly to a full boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanuts and beat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.
Makes 15 to 20.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray muffins pans with Pam. Half each biscuit, place one half in each muffin cup. Then spread small amounts of Ragu, add 2 or 3 slices of pepperoni and shredded cheese then top each one with the other biscuit half. Place in oven and bake until golden.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet before adding batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil potatoes until not quite done. Drain.
Place potatoes in lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add pimientos, peppers and onions; stir.
On the side: slowly melt Velveeta, Cheddar cheese and butter in saucepan. Gradually add 1/2 cup milk and blend all.
Pour sauce over all. Sprinkle with dried bread crumbs, then paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Can be partially baked and reheated.)

title: witches' brew
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to cup of hot water.
Good, good, good.

title: zuppe valdosta(soup of the val d' aosta)
directions: Remove the tough ribs from the cabbage. Drop cabbage into a pan of boiling water and blanch for 5 minutes.
Slice cabbage. Combine in a saucepan with the broth and simmer for 1 hour.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil the raisins, dates and apples in water for 3 minutes. Add shortening to melt and cool.
Add rest of ingredients with nuts last.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a casserole dish. Spread chili over cream cheese and top with shredded pizza cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or bake in microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: loaded baked potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes, water, salt, pepper, basil, parsley flakes, bouillon cubes and onions for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fry bacon and crumble; add to soup.
Use bacon grease and add milk and flour to make gravy.
Add to soup.
Add 2 cans of soup, preferably 1 Cheddar cheese and 1 other to soup.
Stir well and cook another 10 to 15 minutes.
If soup is too thick, you may add more milk.
This makes a lot of soup!

title: spicy beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and garlic; let simmer.
Add taco sauce, tomatoes, chilies and bouillon cubes.
Simmer until bouillon dissolves.
Mix up water and flour.
Pour into ground beef and stir.
Arrange biscuits on top and brown in oven.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop chipped beef into small pieces and save back enough to roll the cheese ball in.
Dice onions very fine.
Combine ingredients by hand and form into a ball.
Roll in remaining chipped beef.

title: ham and sweet potato croquettes
directions: Combine ham and sweet potatoes. Shape into croquettes. Dip into the beaten egg, which has been mixed with the water. Roll in crumbs. Fry in shallow or deep fat or bake until brown in a 400° oven.

title: three cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions for 6 minutes. Drain.
Combine cheese cubes and macaroni in bowl or baking dish and toss.
Fill a 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish with milk to just cover macaroni.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix cherry juice with clear jel and sugar.
Add to cherries and cook in saucepan until thick.
Add almond extract.
Divide between pie crusts and bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: potato nests with peas
directions: In a bowl, combine potatoes and egg yolk; stir in the cheese. Spoon 2 mounds onto a greased baking sheet.
With the back of a spoon, shape each mound into a 4-inch nest.
Top with dill and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.
Fill nests with peas.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until heated through.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in bowl. Spread bean dip on large shallow serving platter.
Top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with Cheddar cheese. Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips.
Makes huge amount.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, mix with other ingredients.

title: cherry angel food trifle
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cream cheese until blended.
Stir Cool Whip into cheese mixture.
Stir this topping into the cake cubes.
Mix well.
Into bowl or 9 x 13-inch container, layer 1/2 cake mixture and 1/2 of cherry pie filling.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple nut ring
directions: Separate the biscuits into 20 pieces.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip biscuits into melted butter, then roll in sugar mixture.
Arrange biscuits around edge of deep dish baker, using a total of 15; overlap remaining 5 biscuits in the center.
Peel, core and slice apples into thin slices.
Place an apple slice between each biscuit and place apple slices all around the outer edge.
Mix nuts and raisins with remaining sugar mixture and pour over all.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Place dates in bowl.
Add boiling water and baking soda.
Stir and let cool.
When dates are cool, add sugar and egg; blend.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Pour in mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: topsy turvy corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes. When meat is done, add tomatoes.
Cover top with corn bread and bake at 350° until browned.
Make a salad and you have a meal!

title: chicken in wine
directions: Soak chicken in beaten eggs at least 3 hours.
Drain and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown in butter in frypan.
Place chicken breasts in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix mushrooms, lemon juice, wine and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Top chicken with cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with long grain rice cooked with green pepper and butter.

title: black bean salad
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook until tender (up to 2 hours). Combine beans, peppers, corn and onions in a bowl.
Gently mix. Mix garlic, lime juice, salt, olive oil and red pepper sauce. Pour over bean mixture.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled eggs. Refrigerate several hours until cold.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Beat egg.
Add onion and pepper (chopped fine).
Add bread after breaking into small pieces.
Add hamburger, salt and black pepper and mix well.
In small bowl mix vinegar, sugar, mustard, tomato puree and water until sugar is dissolved.
Pour 1/4 mixture over meat.
Shape into loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
When done, remove from oven; pour off excess fat and pour remaining tomato mixture over meat.
Return to oven for a few minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in oleo.
Add celery seed.
In casserole dish, mix soups and rice.
Add onion mixture and broccoli, drained.
Spread Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Mix and pack first four ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Dissolve 1 package Knox gelatine and 1/4 cup cold water and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine milk, cornstarch, vanilla, salt, 1 cup sugar, egg yolks and poppy seed. Boil over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine and allow to cool.
Take 5 egg whites and beat with cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold into cooled mixture and pour over crust.
Top with whipped cream, can put chopped nuts on top.
Refrigerate until set about 2 to 3 hours.

title: butterscotch rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle with coarse chopped nuts (pecans); add rolls.
Sprinkle with dry pudding.
Melt and mix together brown sugar and butter.
Pour over rolls.
Cool and let rise overnight or at least 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: belgian braised beef
directions: Put chopped onion and butter into a 3-quart boiler and cook until tender, stirring to keep from scorching, then add the seasoned meat to boiler.
Stir until the meat is brown.
Add one can of beer and one clove of garlic.
Reduce the heat.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Remove the clove of garlic and add flour to thicken gravy.
Add a little water to keep gravy smooth.
Stir constantly.
Remove from the heat.
Serve warm with mashed potatoes, rice or egg noodles.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and place in greased baking dish. Combine crackers and margarine.
Sprinkle over Veg-All mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla; stir over medium heat until thickened (about 12 minutes). Add coconut and pecans; beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Great over German chocolate cake.

title: oyster stew for two
directions: Heat milk and cream to scalding.
Just before serving, melt butter in saucepan.
Add oysters with liquid.
Cook gently, just until oyster edges curl.
Add to scalded milk and cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately with oyster crackers.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in two clean 8 or 9-inch layer pans; prick each cake with large two pronged fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and spoon over cake layers.
Chill 4 hours.
Dip one pan in warm water for 10 seconds; unmold onto serving plate.
Frost.
Unmold second layer; place on first layer.
Frost.
Refrigerate.
Garnish as desired.

title: tea cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Combine salt, flour and baking powder.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture alternately with milk and beat well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Dot with brown sugar and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together and cook 1 minute.
After it starts to boil don't overcook and then add 1/2 jar of peanut butter and put in 2 tablespoons of marshmallow cream.
Mix together and put in pan.

title: buns(boller)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients as for pie crust.
Add sugar to water and sprinkle yeast on top.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add well beaten eggs and yeast mixture to milk.
Mix it all together with flour mixture.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 7 to 9 minutes. Let rise in covered bowl for 1 hour.
Punch down and form into 40 balls.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: ham wrap-ups
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on the ham; make sure you spread it all over the ham slice, then put 1 spear of asparagus at one end.
Roll up and lay it down, with the rolled side down, in a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep making the ham wrap-ups until all ham is used up.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: meltaways
directions: Melt the 1 pound chocolate in the top of a double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat as soon as it is fully melted.
In a small saucepan, bring whipping cream to a boil; measure the temperature with a candy thermometer.
Let whipping cream cool to about 150°, about 1 minute.
Pour the warm, melted chocolate into a large mixing bowl; add melted shortening and mix well.
Add flavoring to hot cream; add the hot cream at one time to the chocolate.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat by hand.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa; add to mixture.
Mix and add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread marshmallow cream over cake and return to oven until melted.
Cool.
(Pan size 9 x 13-inches.)

title: party rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half.
Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together.
Add ham.
Spread on bottom half of rolls.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Place top half of rolls over cheese.
These can be frozen; if you do, thaw completely before heating.
Cook at 300° to 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare noodles; drain and rinse.
Add vegetables and cheese. Add dressing; mix well.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese blintze
directions: Cream the cream cheese, egg yolks and sugar.
Roll bread slices with a rolling pin.
Spread mixture on bread; roll like jelly roll.
Dip in melted butter (2 sticks melted at a time). Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Let cool; cut into bite size pieces.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Mix the milk, pop and pineapple all together at once; put into 1 gallon ice cream freezer.
Pack with crushed ice and salt and turn freezer, about 15 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: drop tea cake cookies
directions: Mix
flour, sugar, butter and Crisco, then add eggs and mix well.
Combine
soda
in
buttermilk and add to first mixture, then
add
flavoring.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Crush and let drain.
Cut cauliflower into small pieces.
Cut onion into small pieces and mix with cauliflower. Drain can of peas and mix in with the peas.
Mix all together, then add the bacon bits.
After well mixed, add mayonnaise to taste.

title: grilled turkey breast
directions: Cut turkey breast in strips with the grain.
Soak overnight or for several hours in remaining ingredients.
Cook on grill.
Baste often until done.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mix well.
Roll into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture.
Put on wax paper.

title: spaghetti casserole(the best!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and onion in large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add mushrooms; simmer and stir 5 minutes.
Add garlic, tomatoes and tomato sauce and simmer 5 more minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and stir.
Pour mixture over spaghetti and mix.
Pour half the mixture into large casserole sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and add remaining spaghetti mixture.
Top with Parmesan and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Recipe makes 8 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in order bread, sausage and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top of cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Then add chili powder, salt, tomato sauce, rice and 1 cup cheese and simmer about 2 minutes.
Pour in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Put Ro-Tel tomatoes with juice on top (cut up tomatoes).
Top this with 1 cup of cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn soup
directions: Boil salt meat for 1/2 hour to get excess salt out; drain and rinse.
Add salt meat and soup meat in pot filled about 3/4 full of water.
Let this come to a full boil and remove bubbles from top of soup until there are none left.
Add seasonings (onion, celery, bell pepper and a little garlic), Ro-Tel, tomatoes, tomato sauce and rice.
Let all of this cook about two hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add as much fresh corn (which has already been cooked), frozen corn (as is in package) or canned corn as you like.
When all of this has come back to a boil, cook another 30 minutes.
Eat and enjoy!

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream
together sugars	and
margarine.
Add
eggs
and vanilla; beat well.
Add
dry
ingredients to creamed mixture. Chill. Divide into thirds. Shape
into 3 bars (2 x 2-inch) and freeze. To cook:
Slice 1/4 inch slices.
Bake at 350° approximately 8 to 10 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mints
directions: Mix all.
Works great in mint molds.
Store in airtight container.
Store in cool place.
Not refrigerator.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Mix well and flour in one 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 320° for 45 minutes.

title: shipwreck
directions: Peel onions; slice and arrange in bottom of 3-quart baking dish or crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Peel potatoes and slice as if to fry.
Put pieces over onions, salt and pepper. Crumble raw hamburger over potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle rice over hamburger.
Pour kidney beans and juice over top.
Spread tomato soup over top and cook 3 hours or all day on low.
DO NOT STIR!

title: apple pudding
directions: In a large bowl, cream the first three items until light and fluffy.
Set aside.
Mix the next three items and blend into first mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured nine-inch square pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: aspirin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn down TV.
Remove toys from countertop.
Measure 2 cups flour.
Remove Nikki's hands from flour.
Vacuum mixture from floor (Melinda spilled).
Get an egg. Answer telephone.
Separate egg.
Grease pan.
Salesman at door. Answer telephone again.
Put baking powder, salt and flour into sifter.
Put mess in sink.
Call the bakery.
Take an aspirin.

title: fire and ice
directions: Place onions, tomatoes and bell pepper in a bowl.
In a saucepan, bring all other ingredients to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute only.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
Good with grilled steaks.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together
with spoon sugar, oil and cinnamon.
Mix dry ingredients and
add to sugar-oil mixture.	Fold in apples and nuts.
Place
in
large
aluminum
pan
and
sprinkle with butterscotch morsels.
Place in oven and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham roll ups
directions: Pat ham slices with paper towel to be sure they are dry. Spread thin layer of softened cream cheese on one side of ham. Place whole gherkin along short side of ham.
Roll across.
Slice the ham roll into 3/4-inch pieces.
Serve.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Put all together in 1 cooking bag.
Put in roaster with cover on.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: mena's orange slice cookies
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients well to coat candy; set aside.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to boil; cook, uncovered, for two minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: country fried potatoes
directions: Heat shortening or oil in heavy skillet over low heat.
Arrange a layer of sliced potatoes and sliced onions; repeat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Uncover and increase heat slightly; saute for 10 minutes longer or until potatoes are crisp and brown on underside.
Do not stir.
Fold in half as with an omelet.
Serve on a hot platter.

title: chicken fruit salad
directions: Place chicken and water in oven; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and remove chicken from bone. Coarsely chop and set aside.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice. Coarsely chop apple.
Dip in pineapple juice to prevent discoloring.
Combine chicken, pineapple, apple, grapes and mayonnaise; mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6.

title: french toast (for a crowd!)
directions: Take 10 slices of bread, cut off crusts and cube. Put 1/2 of the cubes into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Take one package of cream cheese and cube; lay on top of cubed bread. Add remaining cubed bread and second package of cubed cream cheese to top.
Beat eggs well; add maple syrup and fold into eggs.
Add milk.
Pour over bread and cream cheese mixture.
Put into refrigerator overnight.
Bake in the morning at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Press pecans into pie crust.
Bake crust until light brown. Mix soft cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Top with blueberries.
Makes 2 pies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add tomatoes (broken into pieces), salt and sugar.
Cook 5 minutes until thick.
Pour over thinly sliced unpeeled zucchini in greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix well; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° (325° for glass).

title: martha washington jets
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 sugar.
Add egg white (beaten until fluffy, but not stiff).
Gradually add remaining sugar.
Use flavoring, if desired.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on low heat until ball forms, about 3 to 5 minutes and stir.
Let cool.
Knead until smooth. Divide; add food coloring as desired.
Store in airtight container in the fridge.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk and beat until thick. Pour into crust. Top with Cool Whip. Chill.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have 10-inch pie pan ready.
Crumble sausage and lightly brown, breaking up clumps.
Drain fat.
Spoon into pie plate.
Top with hash browns then sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs, milk and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until slightly puffed and knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: simple caramel brownies
directions: Blend eggs, sugar and margarine together.
Then add flour. Add nuts and pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: crisp chewies cookies(like gingersnaps)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine, egg and molasses together.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring the oats last. Drop dough by teaspoonful 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
The cookies will puff up and fall. When done, remove from oven just after they fall.
If cookies are overbaked, they will be crisp, but not chewy.
Allow to stay on cookie sheet for 1 to 2 minutes before removing.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute garlic, onion and fresh parsley in oil for several minutes. Add tomato, sauce, chicken broth, beef broth and spices. Cook over low heat for 30 seconds.
Add tortilla chips and cook for 5 to 10 minutes. Ladle into bowls and top with cheese and fresh diced tomatoes. Serve immediately so the chips don't get too soggy.

title: potatoes and pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Combine sour cream and soup in skillet chops were browned in.
Add onion and water.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Add vegetables, beans and sauce.
Heat through.
Cover with mashed potato mixture. Spread with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and potatoes are set.
Serves 5.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa; boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Blend well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
The cookies will harden and no baking is necessary.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream
cheese
and sugar until blended well.
(Use electric hand beater;
make
sure
mixture is soft.) Add eggs, sour cream and
vanilla;
mix well until smooth.
Pour mixture into graham
cracker
shells (should be filled about halfway). Place on trays and	bake
in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown
on
top.
After
cooling they will shrink into
shells.
Refrigerate
until
cold.	Cover
with
fruit topping of choice.	Cut into 6 or 8 portions and decorate with whipped cream.

title: shrimp fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles. while noodles are cooking melt butter and cream in small saucepan. As soon as butter melts add parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Keep warm over low heat. Drain noodles and return to pan. Pour sauce over. Toss gently until evenly coated. Saute shrimp and garlic in butter. Add shrimp to noodles. Toss and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup with beater.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a large bowl and then add the pecans (freshly shelled, if possible).
In another bowl, vigorously beat the eggs and when they're thick and frothy, add the milk. Stir the beaten egg mixture into the dry ingredients.
Pour the batter into a well-greased 8 x 4-inch wax pan or a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove from the pan and cool on a wire rack.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and cream of tartar in a saucepan.
Mix liquids and gradually stir into dry ingredients.
When mixture is smooth, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until a ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Knead until smooth.
Do not eat!

title: homemade noodles
directions: Make ball; knead.
Round into ball.
Place into bowl.
Let sit 30 minutes.
Split into pieces, 4 or so.
Use lots of flour to keep dough from sticking to anything.
Roll out into a large sheet (thin).
Let sit another 30 minutes or so.
Flour well.
Take one sheet, place on board, flour top of sheet; place another on top and also flour.
Roll up and press into place a little.
Take a knife or some sharp cutter and cut at any width you prefer, 1 1/2-inches.
Let noodles dry more extensively.
Then either store or cook.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add chili beans, Mexican style sauce and water.
Cook 15 minutes.
Roll or pat biscuits out and form over bottom side of muffin pans (greased) to make cups.
Bake cups.
Put meat sauce in.
Top with cheese, lettuce, taco sauce, etc.

title: cherry hot-cold dessert
directions: Sift flour, sugar,
salt
and baking powder.
Add milk. Pour batter into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cherries and 3/4 cup sugar, pour over batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and both sugars.
Add oil; cream.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Make into balls.
Roll in sugar; flatten out with a glass dipped in sugar.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar and milk on low heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Start timing and boil 7 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add marshmallows and peanut butter.
Pour into a large pan that has been buttered.
This hardens fast, so have everything ready and work fast when removed from heat.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until very tender.
Remove skins.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue cooking for about 30 minutes or until silver knife comes out clean.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop in hot oil and fry about 5 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute onions in half of margarine.
Mix all other ingredients together, except crushed corn flakes and half of margarine.
Pour in a large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch).
Melt the remaining margarine and combine with corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of potato mixture and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage to desired consistency.
Add drained pineapple; save juice.
Mix juice with 1 cup mayonnaise and mix with cabbage. Even the kids love it.

title: myra's southern pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and then add flavoring.
Set aside.
In another bowl, sift flour with baking powder.
Alternate adding evaporated milk and flour mixture to the butter mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pop's fried rice
directions: 1. Heat wok with oil, ginger, garlic and salt over high heat for 10 seconds.

title: crawfish and pasta
directions: Peel crawfish tails, reserving heads.
Make a stock by boiling heads in 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Saute tails and green onions in butter until hot.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of the stock and the cream.
Heat but do not boil.
Should be slightly thick.
Cook pasta.
Add sauce and toss.
Heat over medium heat.
Serve immediately.
Shrimp can be used in place of crawfish.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Hershey bars and chocolate chips.
Then add Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Pour into buttered dish and cool.
Makes 5 pounds of candy.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour. Fry in oil. When cool, place in a baking dish. Bring rest of ingredients to a boil (except lemon juice). Add the lemon juice after you take pot off heat. Pour the sauce over the chicken in the baking dish. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes. Turn after about 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: *Or can use cranberries instead of rhubarb.

title: valentine cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Prepare crust (below) and place in freezer for 5 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together, except cheese and potato chips.
Put into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle grated cheese over top, then potato chips. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May need to double recipe.

title: inexpensive punch
directions: Do not use sugar if you use presweetened Kool-Aid.
Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale, and place in freezer.
Stir often.
Do not freeze solid; let make slush.
Add the ginger ale just before serving.

title: cole slaw souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Blend in mayonnaise, cold water, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Beat until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or a 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold and garnish with radish slices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry until crisp.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper; blend well.
Add water and vinegar and stir.
Cook until thickened.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly. Serve warm.

title: egyptian cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate in 5 teaspoons boiling water.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk; mix thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Grease three layer cake pans.
Bake at 350°
until done for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil.
Boil and stir five minutes more.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Stir in vanilla and cut-up nuts.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press mixture firmly against bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Melt butter in microwave and stir in other ingredients.
Place chicken in casserole.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream corn muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray muffin pan with vegetable oil spray.
Fill each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: e-z cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add 2 Tbsp. (+/-) water.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dhahran crescent rolls
directions: Combine the yeast and warm water. Mix together the salt, sugar, powdered milk, eggs, melted butter, flour and yeast mixture.
Mix in mixer with dough hooks for 3 or 4 minutes or knead by hand 10 to 12 minutes.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours in greased bowl in oven (with light on only). Cut dough in half. Roll each half out to circle. Spread with melted butter. Cut in fourths. Cut each fourth in half.
Start at big end and roll up crescent. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 32 crescent rolls.

title: seafood salad deluxe
directions: Cook noodles until tender. Drain and let them cool. Chop crab sticks and shrimp in bite size pieces. Separate crabmeat.
Chop celery.
In a large bowl, add the chopped celery, parsley flakes and Hellmann's mayonnaise to the seafood.
Chill for 1/2 hour. Ingredients may be added to your taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain the spinach.
Mix all ingredients together. Form into small balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Pour into ice cream maker. With 2 bags of ice and 1 box of rock salt and a towel to cover ice cream maker, mix thoroughly.
Let sit for 30 minutes before serving.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Whip milk until light and fluffy.
Add softened cream cheese and whip until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Fold in cheese and chill.

title: italian beef
directions: Add more garlic powder, oregano and onion to flavor to your taste.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook at least 6 hours.
Remove meat and flake with fork.
Put meat back into crock-pot and let simmer for another 10 to 20 minutes.
Serve on poor boy buns with Mozzarella cheese.

title: creamy dilled carrots
directions: In a saucepan, combine carrots, water, butter, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cover and simmer until carrots are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain liquid into a small saucepan; set the carrots aside and keep warm.
Bring liquid to a boil.
In a small bowl, combine flour and cream until smooth; slowly add to liquid, stirring constantly.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over carrots; stir in dill.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin bread pudding
directions: Place bread on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Turn; bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until dry. Cut into cubes (should have about 4 cups).
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add pumpkin, milk, sugar and spices.
Mix well; then add bread cubes.
Let sit for 5 minutes; then add raisins.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: bean salad(stefanich's restaurant, estero island, off ft.  myers, florida)
directions: In a large bowl combine the beans.
In a quart jar combine the remaining ingredients.
Cover and shake together thoroughly.
Pour over beans.
Mix together gently.
Chill overnight or for several hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 persons.

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: Combine chicken and cheese. Mix well.
Separate rolls.
Place equal amounts of chicken and cheese mixture on wide end of each triangle.
Roll around mixture.
Place rolls in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine soup, milk and remaining cheese-chicken mixture.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over baked rolls.
Serves 4.

title: american-mexican goulash
directions: Cook ground beef; drain grease.
Add all other ingredients, but cheese.
Simmer until chili is well blended.
Add cheese; simmer until cheese is melted and blended.
Serve over chips. Garnish with shredded lettuce, green onions and tomatoes.
Serve hot.
May double or triple for large crowds.

title: cheddar corn
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute, stirring frequently.
Add corn, milk, pepper, salt, sugar and pepper.
Heat to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in Cheddar cheese just until melted.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Wash potatoes and boil well until done.
Skin at once.
Mash 2 1/4 pounds.
Add salt, cornstarch and boiling milk.
Dough will be soft at first but will become firmer as it cools.
Dice, roll and fry until golden brown.
With floured hands, shape the potato dough into dumplings.
Press into each ball a few croutons.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Simmer until done.
Cooking time is 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well. Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Sift flour, a little at a time. Roll out and cut out.
Put on cooking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peach or apple pie
directions: Slice fruit in pie crust.
Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over fruit.
Add water.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Cook on 350° for 15 minutes and then on 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: cream velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, creaming well while adding.
Then add salt and water alternately with cake flour in which has been sifted baking powder.
Last, fold in the beaten whites of the eggs.
Add vanilla.
Bake in layers.

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large pan, melt butter, sugar and water until butter is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate until melted.
Pour into bowl and let stand for 10 minutes until slightly cool.
Beat eggs in one at a time on high speed.
Then add dry ingredients on low speed until blended. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Roll teaspoons of dough into balls.
Place 2 inches apart.
Cook 11 to 12 minutes (no longer).
Remove immediately and place mint on each cookie (use 1/2 mint).
Allow mint to soften and swirl over cookie.

title: clock watcher's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve in lettuce-lined salad bowl or on individual lettuce beds.
Serves 6.

title: mrs. bonsell's nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into a long roll in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Very good and makes lots.

title: apple ring pickles
directions: First Step:
Peel, core and cut in rings 1/2-inch thick the cucumbers.
Mix lime with water and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese, egg yolk, sugar and flavoring.
Spread on bread slices.
Roll up; dip in melted butter and roll in a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon lover's tart
directions: In top of double boiler set over, but not touching simmering water, combine the eggs, egg yolks and sugar.
Whisk until the mixture is pale yellow, about 10 minutes.
Whisk in butter, piece by piece, allowing each to melt before adding the next.
Add grated lemon zest and lemon juice, whisking frequently until mixture is thick and the first bubbles appear, about 10 minutes longer:
do not let it boil.
Pour filling into lemon pastry shell.
Smooth with a spatula.
Set aside at room temperature until filling firms up, about 30 minutes, before unmolding and serving.
Garnish with lemon zest strips.
Fresh blueberries, raspberries and/or strawberries are a beautiful garnish as well.
Serves 8.

title: bubbles
directions: You will also need baby food jars and pipe cleaners.

title: mother's tea cakes
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Add flour which has been sifted with baking soda.
Add vanilla flavoring.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugars, butter, eggs and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture and mix until all blended. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Mix the egg white and water together, but do not beat.
Add pecans and stir until pecans are well coated.
Mix the sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon together and cover pecans with this mixture. Bake on buttered foil-lined pan at 350° for about 30 minutes, stirring several times.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chinese chews
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.

title: shortbread
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Cut in softened butter.
Place in 2 balls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten into 7-inch circles, about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Flute edges.
Prick lines on circle with a fork.

title: one bowl peanut butter bread
directions: Make a paste of 2 1/2 Tbsp. cornstarch and 1 Tbsp flour; add to above mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in 1/2 c. peanut butter.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.

title: green bean casserole
