directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, blend soup, milk and pepper. Stir in beans and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Based on 4 servings.

title: dipping chocolate
directions: Put wax and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Place over hot water.
Heat over medium heat.
Never melt wax over direct heat. Stir until chocolate is melted and well blended.
Remove double boiler from heat.
Insert double pronged kitchen fork into bottom of fondant egg or place egg on a flat wire skimmer.
Dip into chocolate.
Let excess chocolate drip for a moment.
Carefully place egg on wax paper cookie sheet.
Stir chocolate before dipping each egg.
If chocolate thickens, place over low heat.

title: spanish dip
directions: Drain spinach, press to remove excess liquid.
Combine with sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix and water chestnuts in bowl; mix well.
Chill until serving time.

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Cut French bread lengthwise.
Butter and put under broiler to toast.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Mix in tomato paste and oregano.
Spread beef mixture on bread.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Spread cheese on top of tomatoes.
Place in broiler to melt cheese.
Cut and serve.

title: veggie casserole
directions: While vegetables are cooking, brown onion in margarine.
Add together all other ingredients.
Mix in onion and veggies.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a pot on top of the stove bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar and salt.
Beat well, then add sour cream, eggs and soda.
Mix well and pour into a greased cookie sheet (with sides about 1 inch).

title: bride delight
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add beaten egg yolks; blend until light yellow.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add a little flour and milk alternately until you have used 2/3 of the flour.
Mix baking powder with remainder of the flour; continue with the rest of the milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Use 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes. Frost with favorite icing.

title: pumpkin biscuits
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl and cut in shortening.
Stir in sugar and pumpkin and mix well.
Pat to 1-inch thickness on a floured board and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: dark fruitcake
directions: Grease three 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans or two 10 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Line bottom and sides of pans with brown paper to prevent overbrowning.
Grease paper.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice and drain tomato (place tomato on paper towel and lightly sprinkle with salt, then let set 5 minutes).
Line pan with pie crust; bake pie crust only for 10 minutes.
Spread cheese onto pie crust, then onion.
Arrange tomato on top; sprinkle with spices and oil.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom potato casserole
directions: Cook whole potatoes in boiling salted water 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and slightly cool.
Peel and slice about 1/2 inch thick.
Set aside.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach using 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Drain. Mash out all liquid.
Combine spinach, soup, egg and cheese. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs into butter to which garlic and red pepper have been added.
Place on top of spinach and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.
Great!

title: kara's chili
directions: Brown meat (beef and sausage) with garlic and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Place meat mixture in crockpot and add remaining ingredients.
Add small amount of water, if necessary.
Cook on "low", 6-7 hours.
Serves 8-10.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth, about 30 to 60 seconds. Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: italian hamburgers
directions: Sprinkle the ground beef lightly with the salt. Add the onion and pepper.
Mix well and shape into large round patties.
Place in shallow pan. Add oregano.
Cover hamburger patties with the spaghetti sauce. Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve on hot sesame seed buns.

title: rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large, warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal creamies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening with raisins, sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add oatmeal and milk.
Bake at 350°.

title: angelio's coney sauce
directions: Combine everything except hot dogs.
Simmer until thick.
Stir in hot dogs.
Cook 15 minutes longer.
Store in freezer bags. Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: simply good apple dessert
directions: Peel, core and slice apples; layer evenly in shallow 1 quart microwave-safe casserole.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
In a microwave-safe 1-cup measure, microwave margarine on High (100% power) for 1 minute or until margarine is melted.
Drizzle over apple mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 1/2 to 7 1/2 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cut beets when sauce is thick and add to syrup.
Add 1 tablespoon butter last.

title: so simple barbecue chicken or pork chops
directions: Place cut up fryer in large pot and season with salt.
Mix sauce and Coca-Cola together until it mostly covers meat.
Cook on top of range (medium heat) until tender; approximately 45 minutes.

title: holiday bread dressing
directions: Mix with 1/2 to 3/4 cup water ingredients listed.
Can be cooked alone in side dish or used to stuff poultry.
Cook until celery is tender and dish is browned, if cooked alone.

title: asparagus with water chestnuts
directions: Wash and trim asparagus, breaking off woody portion near root. Cut asparagus diagonally into 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Parboil in slightly salted water until nice green color.
Drain. Saute asparagus and water chestnuts in butter and season to taste. Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour water into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with roasting rack.
In a small saucepan, mix honey, olive oil and curry powder; bring to a boil.
Place chicken on rack, breast side up.
Brush with honey mixture.
Spoon 2 teaspoons of mixture into center cavity and sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.

title: lamingtons
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until mixture is thick and sugar completely dissolved. Sift dry ingredients several times.
Melt butter in hot water. Sift dry ingredients over egg mixture.
Fold in lightly.
Then working quickly, fold in hot water and butter.
Pour into lightly greased 18 cm x 28 cm (7 x 11-inch) lamington tin.
Bake in moderate oven at approximately 30 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Cook Jell-O, crushed pineapple and sugar 2 minutes.
Let cool. Whip cream cheese and water.
Stir this into the cooled Jell-O mixture.
When set, stir in a box of Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, sugar, eggs, peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press nut or kiss into each or press with finger to put jelly or jam.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: five minute fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, saving 1 cup juice.
Mix juice, fruit, pudding and lemon juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, slice bananas into it.

title: vegetable dish
directions: Cook package of frozen vegetables until half done and drain. Add celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir well and then add water chestnuts.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Dot with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Put ice cream in ice cream maker.
Turn until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil hens.
Take meat from bones and grind.
Season with salt while hens are cooking.
Cut up celery, pickles, apples, eggs and pimentos.
Add Miracle Whip dressing.
May add black pepper and more salt, if needed.
Can also use bell pepper, if desired.
Hens are best for making this salad.
Grind the chicken instead of cutting it up.
This makes a lot of difference.
A large serving tablespoon of sweet relish may also be added.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter; mix until smooth.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use ungreased cookie sheets.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and almond extract.
With mixer on low speed, beat in flour just until well blended.
Add food coloring, a small amount at a time, beating well after each addition.
Spoon 1 cup dough into cookie press or pastry bag.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes, until bottoms of cookies are lightly brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Spread between layers, sides and top.

title: corn and beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion together.
Cook noodles; combine with soup, cheese and water.
Mix all together; place in casserole. Cover with corn.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Beat well.
Add eggs, sugar, oil, vanilla and pumpkin.
Beat very well.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare your favorite pastry shell; refrigerate.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large mixing bowl. Add the pumpkin, molasses and melted butter and blend well. Slightly beat the eggs; add eggnog to the eggs.
Pour into pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Stir in brandy.
Pour into the pastry shell. Bake in 425° oven for 40 minutes or until silver knife inserted comes out clean.

title: skillet sausage supper
directions: In hot butter in skillet, saute green pepper just until edges start to brown.
Drain corn; add to pepper with pimentos and chili powder.
Now add drained Vienna sausages; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until thoroughly heated.
Serve right in skillet.
Makes 2 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put oil in baking dish.
Place chicken breasts in pan sprinkled with Nature's Seasons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Add ingredients in order listed and mix.
Pour into pans 1/2 inch from top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in small pans and 55 minutes in regular pans.

title: cinnamon rolls(the quick, easy way with pillsbury hot roll mix)
directions: Prepare Pillsbury hot roll mix according to directions.
After dough is mixed and allowed to stand the required 5 minutes, roll it into a long rectangle, approximately 9 x 15-inches, with rolling pin.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water to light syrup.

title: german chocolate cheese cake
directions: Blend cake mix, coconut, butter and eggs on low speed until crumbly.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Toss together lightly and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1 can of chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp spaghetti(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add cleaned, sliced mushrooms and garlic (minced).
Saute until garlic is tender.
Add cleaned, raw shrimp.
Continue to saute until shrimp turns pink.
Add whipping cream.
Keep under a boil for 10 to 15 minutes or until vermicelli is cooked.
Serve over vermicelli with lots of Parmesan cheese sprinkled on it.

title: country style steak
directions: Salt and pepper steaks.
Coat with flour.
Fry in hot shortening until medium brown.
Remove steaks from pan.
Add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls flour to hot grease. Let it start turning brown.
Return steaks to this and add water, a little at a time, to cover steaks.
Turn burner down to simmer or slow boil for 20 minutes.
If gravy gets too low, add a little extra water carefully though, it may become too thin.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Blend margarine and flour.
Add broth, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add sour cream and chilies.
Do not boil.
Soften tortillas.
Fill with cheese and onion.
Pour gravy over top and add cheese.
Cover with foil.
Before placing in dish, spoon a little gravy on bottom of dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg, then coat with bread crumbs.
Heat oil in a skillet over medium-low heat and cook chicken 15 minutes or until brown on both sides and no longer pink.
Remove from oil and keep warm.
Pour off fat.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) clear plastic cups.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell per directions and set aside to cool.
Mash 1 cup of berries.
Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Add slowly the water and mashed strawberries.
(Cut medium stirring as you go until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Cool.) Beat cream cheese until smooth, spread on pie shell.
Fill shell with remaining berries.
Pour cooked berry mixture over top and chill for 3 hours.
(This adds a bit of a surprise to blueberry pie!)

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Dust chicken with flour and salt.
Brown in oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except pineapple and cornstarch, but including the juice from pineapple, to chicken and simmer until celery is done.
Add pineapple chunks.
Thicken with cornstarch.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Grind onions in processor.
Blend together onions, butter and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Grind onions in processor.
Blend and mix together.
Spray pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good.
Dip on Club crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients together; put into casserole dish. Top with cheese and onion rings or bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Add egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat into a smooth thin batter.
Fold in apples.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle topping over pie and return to oven and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pizza bread
directions: Cover bread (rub with oil) and thaw for about 6 hours.
Roll each loaf into a 13 x 17-inch rectangle.
Beat eggs with Parmesan cheese (reserve about 1/4 cup).
Spread mixture on bread.
Layer pepperoni, then cheese.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet and brush with reserved egg mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with heated pizza sauce for a dip.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat and onion in hot oil.
Add rest of ingredients, except bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and water chestnuts.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Pour off liquid and save it.
Put 1 cup of sugar in pickles and pour liquid over it and shake.
Refrigerate overnight and ready for use.

title: berries and cream
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth. Mix with angel food cake.
Then bring cornstarch, dry jello, sugar and water to a boil.
Cook until it thickens.
Cool and pour over cake mixture.
Top with strawberries.

title: molded french cream
directions: Brush one 4-cup decorative mold with vegetable oil.
Combine sour cream and heavy cream in a medium saucepan.
Beat in sugar; place over very low heat to warm.
Sprinkle gelatin over water in a cup to soften.
Place cup in a saucepan with hot water to dissolve and liquify.
Stir into the warm cream mixture.
Remove from heat. Beat the cream cheese until smooth in a medium-size bowl with electric mixer.
Stir in the cream mixture gradually with the vanilla, blending thoroughly.

title: sully's steak sandwiches
directions: Barbecue flank steak to taste; recommend medium-rare.
Slice steak lengthwise in strips very thinly. They come out conveniently in hot dog bun size.
Heat butter and stir in steak strips. Serve in hot dog buns for delicious change of pace from hot dogs.
A Sullivan Family favorite for 2 generations.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add sweet potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture; add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Pour mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Spread with icing while warm.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix all but peanut butter and oats in pan.
Cook until starts to boil.
Let stand one minute. Mix in oats and peanut butter. Spoon out on wax paper.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Arrange the toast in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle the raisins over the toast.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla.
Pour the mixture over the toast and let stand for 10 minutes.
In a cup, combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle the mixture over the dish.
Bake the pudding at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serve the pudding topped with Lemon Sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add eggs and cream.
Then add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to first mixture and put in carrots and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake in 300° oven for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all with a spoon.
Finish mixing by using your hands, kneading like dough.
Roll into small balls.
Stores in refrigerator.
Great snack for toddlers.

title: big ma's plain cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Add dry ingredients; alternate with milk. Add flavoring. Pour in greased cake pan and place in a cold oven (not too near top of oven). Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Test with straw.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: In a large bowl, combine orange liqueur, juice concentrate, sugar and orange peel.
Mix well.
Add fruit.
Toss gently to combine. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: chicken dumpling pie
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients, pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Stir together baking mix, sour cream and milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until topping is golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick and sticky pecan rolls
directions: Grease a 12-cup muffin tin lightly.
Place a Brown 'N Serve roll in each cup.
Cut an X in the top of each roll.
Tuck 2 pecan halves in cuts.
Melt butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Spoon over rolls.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix ingredients with a beater; pour into a pitcher.
Let cool and serve with ice cream.

title: walnut squares
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in brown sugar and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt and soda.
Mix in walnuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top has dull crust.
Cut while still warm.
Cool and remove from pan.
Yields 32 squares.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Cut up artichokes; add mayonnaise and cheese mix.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Add corn muffin mix.
Pour into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; bake for 45 minutes.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cook bacon cut in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Tastes better the next day.
Reheat in microwave.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and cream cheese together until fluffy.
Add sugar.
Mix well until fluffy.
Add eggs alternately with flour, ending with flour.
Add the vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: florentine beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, mushrooms, garlic and oregano in olive oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in flour.
Add beef broth and cook until thickened. Stir in sour cream.
Add drained spinach.
Put meat mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut cheese into strips and place on top of meat, crisscrossing the strips to decorate.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until casserole is heated through and cheese is just melted.

title: pastry pie shell
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into a ball of dough. Knead the dough until it gets hard enough to roll out.
Divide it in half; roll it out.
Put in pan.
Makes 2 pastry pie shells.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in 1 cup water for 5 minutes. Add instant rice, then add Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning, water and hot sauce.
Mix well.
Add refried beans.
Heat thoroughly.

Heat flour shells in their original plastic bag for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes in microwave or wrap tightly in foil and put in a 450° oven. Dividing meat mixture evenly, put a scoop in each shell with one slice of cheese and onion, if you like.
Fold left and right sides in 1 to 2 inches, then roll.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks; beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour into three greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.
Can use one large pan instead of layers.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add flour, eggs, milk and pineapple.
Mix thoroughly.
Add potatoes and hand stir into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken spiral pasta salad
directions: Mix cracker meal with the pepper, parsley and thyme.
Dip chicken breasts in Butter Buds mixture, then dip into cracker crumb/seasoning mixture (in a separate bowl).
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet in preheated 400° oven for about 25 minutes. (Turn chicken over after 12 minutes.)
While chicken is cooling, boil pasta and lightly steam vegetables and diced red pepper.

Mix the yogurt, Miracle Whip, low-fat milk and Good Seasons salad dressing mix, or use your own seasoning, in blender or processor. When chicken breast is cooked, cut into thin slices or chunks and toss everything together in a large serving bowl.
Serve chilled. Serves 6.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Meatballs:
Mix hamburger meat, sour cream, Ritz crackers, Lipton onion soup mix and eggs together.
Roll into small balls and bake until brown. Drain grease and put into pot with sauce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Gradually add the remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can put icing, coconut or colored sugar on them.

title: toffee pecan bars
directions: Set oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Combine flour and oil.
Cook until lightly browned.
Stir in bacon; cook 1 minute.
Add onion, pepper and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Add the next 8 ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes, until chicken is tender.
Add okra the last 10 minutes of cooking.
Stir in file.
Serve over rice.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first five ingredients to soft ball stage; add vanilla. Cool.
Beat.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll out on floured surface; cut and brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes according to size.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Place flours
and
salt

a large bowl and mix well. Add yeast, dissolved in 3/4 cup lukewarm water; add sugar, mix well and blend in remaining water.
Turn out on floured board. Knead until dough

pans and let rise until double in bulk. Bake 40 minutes or until well browned in 375° oven.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
In an oblong baking dish, shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on Medium power for 20 to 24 minutes.
Drain liquid occasionally. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen curry sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the onion, celery, garlic and curry powder in margarine about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in cornstarch and bouillon granules. Blend in tomato paste. Stir in water and applesauce. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Remove from heat. Cool saucepan quickly in ice water, stirring occasionally.
Pour into 1 1/2 cup containers and freeze.

title: baked potato stuffed with shrimp
directions: Cook shrimp and bake potatoes.
Carefully cut lengthwise in half and scoop out the potatoes, leaving the empty shell.
Whip together with the potatoes the remaining ingredients.
Stuff the mixture into the shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika over the potatoes before serving.
Makes 8 halves.

title: dad's "scratch" hot cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add 3/4 of the water to make a rather thick mixture.

Add egg and mix. Add shortening and mix. Add more water or flour, if necessary, to make batter of desired consistency. Fry in greased frying pan at medium-low heat, turning when bubbles begin to appear in cakes.
Makes 8 to 10 medium size 4-inch cakes.
Serve with margarine, syrup, jelly, honey or whatever.

title: sylvia's minestrone soup
directions: Bring stock to a rolling boil.
Then add the salt, black pepper, oregano, parsley, carrots, celery, cabbage, onions and spinach.
When the carrots have cooked (about 30 minutes), then add the diced tomatoes and the tomato paste.
Cook for another 10 minutes.
Then add the salad macaroni, garbanzo beans and the kidney beans.
Cook until macaroni is done.
Turn off heat.
Let stand for an hour before serving.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and garlic toast.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Spread beans in an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Place slices of Velveeta all over top.
Melt in microwave.
Chill. Spread sour cream. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and chopped chives. Chill several hours or overnight.
Before serving, set at room temperature until it softens.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in microwave; add sugars, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs and beat until well mixed.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Dough will be heavy.
You may have to use your hands.
Chill about 1 hour.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork (crisscross).
Bake at 350° for 14 to 18 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In microwavable bowl, melt chocolate and margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa powder and evaporated milk.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir with wire whisk.
Cook longer if thicker sauce is desired.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef and peppers
directions: Put steak, cut in cubes, in skillet; brown.
Pour off any excess fat.
Mix together and pour over beef the tomatoes (roughly diced), garlic and pepper.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour, until meat is almost tender.
Add sliced onion and green pepper. Cover; cook 30 minutes longer, or until both meat and vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: orange drop doughnuts
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks, milk and orange juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add grated orange peel.
Drop by teaspoon into hot grease; fry about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in powdered sugar or cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: chicken divan casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth and bubbly. Stir in chicken broth with wire whisk. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (4 to 5 minutes). Continue boiling 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and milk until cheese is melted. Add curry powder. Stir well. Combine cooked spaghetti, chicken, broccoli and mushrooms in greased 2-quart casserole. Add cheese mixture. Top with remaining cheese on top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly around edge.

title: mac and stuff
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: mock pound cake
directions: Cream shortening gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add 1 egg at a time and beat each in thoroughly before adding the next. This mixture must be beaten thoroughly.
(If once in a while it may separate, never mind.
The cake will be the better for it.)

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla and stick of margarine together for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and continue to beat.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Place over creamed layer.
Spoon pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts.
Chill 4 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: sue albers' mexican salsa
directions: Chop finely in food processor or by hand the cilantro, chilies and jalapeno peppers.
Use food processor to crush tomatoes. Chill a few hours to allow flavors to blend before first serving. This is a large batch; however, it keeps well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand for at least 4 hours before serving.

title: mandarin layer pudding
directions: To be made in advance.
Arrange half the cookies in base of straight-sided glass dish.
Pour juice from first can over cookies.
Place mandarin oranges over.
Whip the cream and sugar until fairly stiff.
Divide in half; spread over first layer. Repeat layers; decorate and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli until tender (boil in 1-inch of water for 6 minutes) or use frozen; drain.
Mix in one stick of butter or margarine and Velveeta cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix above ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in a shallow pan and cover with sauce.
Bake at 350 for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash and onion and mash well.
Drain well.
Add mayonnaise, crushed crackers, eggs, cheese and Hidden Valley dressing mix.
Mix well and pour into a greased casserole dish. Top with crushed Better Cheddar crackers that have been mixed with liquid margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven or until firm.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, brown sugar and salt.
Make a well in center.
In separate bowl, combine milk, eggs, vanilla and melted butter; cool slightly.
Add to flour mixture; stir with fork until just combined.
Fold in nuts and chips; stir as little as possible.
Divide batter equally into lined muffin pan. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.

title: pineapple and cottage cheese salad
directions: Add the lime Jell-O and lemon Jell-O to 2 cups boiling water and set aside to cool.
(Be sure to use only 2 cups water as the liquid in the pineapple will also be used.) When Jell-O has started to set, add the remaining ingredients and let set in refrigerator until set.

title: easy tacos
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers in a large pan.
Drain excess grease.
Add soups, salt and taco seasoning.
Stir well. Simmer 15 minutes on medium-low heat, stirring occasionally. Serve in warm taco shells.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: midge's chili sauce
directions: Cut up peeled tomatoes.
In large kettle, add tomatoes, chopped onions, pepper, celery, spices, etc.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Pour into clean hot jars and seal.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Melt butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir in 2 tablespoons water and remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until fluffy the cream cheese, salt and light cream.
Blend in first mixture and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread on layers.

title: gosh
directions: Be careful of your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such as have been raised in a good moral atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity; keep warm with a steady fire of devotion and serve with peaches and cream. When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and butter to a boil (medium heat).
Cook 1 minute or until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat; add evaporated milk.
Return to heat; boil 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Combine with rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ellen's prosciutto bread
directions: Roll out the pizza dough.
Add black pepper while rolling dough into large 12-inch circle.
Sprinkle the remaining ingredients over rolled dough.
Sprinkle with black pepper to taste.
Roll into long loaf; brush top of loaf with a little olive oil.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until slightly golden (approximately 45 minutes).

title: miracle chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Cool, stirring frequently, until ready to spread.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together and cool.
Beat eggs and add sugar, mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased pan at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: lemon bonbons
directions: Cream 1 cup butter.
Gradually add 1/3 cup powdered sugar, beating well.
Add flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Add pecans. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Flatten each cookie with the bottom of a glass which has been lightly dipped in flour.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until edges are light brown.
Cool.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.
Cover cake with Marshmallow Creme while hot.
Cool before icing.

title: homemade pizza, new york style
directions: Dissolve yeast with water.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and oil. Add yeast and water.
Knead the dough for 10 minutes. Cover. Let rise double.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix drained pineapple, sugar and flour.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of mixture.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to make a cup.
Sprinkle on top of cheese. Melt 1 stick butter; pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maine cucumber relish
directions: Pare, remove seeds and cut cucumbers in 1-inch squares.
Add onion.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Rinse well.

title: cheddar appetizer spritz crackers
directions: Thoroughly blend first 3 ingredients.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Force through cookie press on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until edges are light golden brown.
Makes approximately 8 dozen appetizers.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Add jar of pizza sauce and simmer until boiling point.
Place on hamburger buns; add cheese.
Place in oven until cheese melts and is hot.

title: chili for 100
directions: Brown onions and meat in fat.
Add all other ingredients except beans and simmer until thoroughly done.
Add beans about half-hour before serving time or at least do not cook so long that beans become mushy.
If mixture seems too thin, you can thicken with gravy thickening.
Garlic may be added, if desired.

title: lemonade
directions: Dissolve sugar in half of the water.
Make sure seeds are removed from juice and then add to water.
Add other half of the water and mix well.
Serve over ice.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: winky dinks
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add cheese until melted.
Spread on party rye bread.
Warm before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on serving plate.	Combine Bacos, ketchup, and horseradish sauce and spread on top of cream cheese.
Combine next 3 ingredients and spread on top of ketchup mixture.
Top with grated cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.

title: stromboli
directions: Thaw bread according to directions on package.
Roll out dough.
Place pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley on dough.
Roll up and baste with mixture of 1 egg, mixed with a small amount of water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix ingredients to the consistency of thick gravy.
Use paintbrush.
Go nuts!

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: *One cup non-fat yogurt can be substituted.

title: chocolate sauce 1
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Makes 2 cups.

title: 5 minute creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut.
Fold into whipped topping.
Chill for 1 hour or more after pouring into graham cracker crust.

title: peach fruitcake
directions: In very large mixing bowl, stir together flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in fruits and peels, nuts and raisins.
Add peaches, milk, mincemeat and brandy; mix well. Turn into 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a 300° oven for 2 hours or until done.
Cool completely; remove from pans.
Wrap in foil or clear plastic wrap and store in a cool place.
Makes 2 fruitcakes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Tear lettuce; add celery, green onions and drained mandarin oranges.
Add slivered almonds caramelized in sugar.

title: eggplant
directions: Put onion and pepper in hot oil and brown slightly.
Add eggplant and garlic; cook a few minutes.
Add tomatoes.
May also be baked for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Sprinkle onion flakes over potatoes.
Melt remaining ingredients, stirring often.
Pour over potatoes and refrigerator set for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Set out on counter 3 to 4 hours before baking.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
A dish that is always part of Potluck Christmas; also a welcome addition to many family gatherings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef; add next 6 ingredients and simmer about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 Fritos and stir well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover well with cheese, then top with rest of Fritos.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell (9-inch).

title: pork and shrimp stir-fry
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water for about 5 minutes; rinse under hot water and drain well.
Heat the oil in a wok or large frying pan; stir-fry the pork for 5 minutes, until almost cooked.
Add the carrot; cook 1 minute.
Add the bell pepper, bean sprouts, snow peas and soy sauce; cook for 2 minutes.
Add the noodles and the shrimp; toss over the heat for 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed, using a 13 x 9 pan. Combine milk, sugar and 1 package of coconut and bring to a boil. Pour over hot cake while mixture is hot; cool. Put tub of Cool Whip on cake and sprinkle on 1 package of coconut. Refrigerate.

title: irish soda bread i
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add butter.
Mix like pie dough with fingers.
Add raisins.
Add buttermilk and eggs to make dough. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans or pie pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Brush with butter straight from oven.

title: steamed vegetables with chicken(china)
directions: Cube chicken into 1/2 inch pieces. Combine 3 Tbsp. of sherry and 1 Tbsp. soy sauce into a mid size bowl. Add chicken and marinate for 1 hour or overnight, the longer the better flavor. Pour enough water in a wok to be just below the steaming rack, bring water to a boil. Add chicken, mushrooms, and water chestnuts into wok and cook for 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Add snow peas and cook for 2-3 minutes or until peas turn bright green. In a medium saucepan combine remaining sherry, soy sauce, water, oyster sauce, cornstarch and sesame oil, mix. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until sauce thickens. Serve chicken over rice with sauce spooned over top. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Shape into balls.
Place in flat pan, one layer to a pan. Cover with sauce and bake.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, place cooled macaroni, add all remaining ingredients, then add mayonnaise to your taste.
Add garlic salt or any seasoning you desire.
Have fun with this salad.
Add or delete to your liking.
